text:
want to know a little inside secret about me? 
when i feel overwhelmed with life, i do nothing. i crawl into a hole and avoid all things! 🙈

i can’t remember a time in my life where i’ve handled my overwhelming feelings differently. to some it looks like procrastination, or laziness and to others it looks like avoidance. i guess you can say that for me it’s all of those things! 
my overwhelming triggers come in all forms! a messy chaotic house, trying to help all the people, the piles of school papers and forms on the kitchen counter top, and so much more... last week in particular it was really bad. i’m not even sure why! it could have been the weather changing, the lack of sunshine in the morning and at night, or even just the fact that my to do list is crazy long! today i started to feel it creep back in again! 
in years past i would feel myself pulling away, hiding from the tasks, feeling overwhelmed and shutting down and it took forever to climb back out from that. 
today i’m able to realize what it feels like and i’m able to grab the reins and respond sooner. does it mean that the overwhelming feeling leave? not necessarily!!!! for me i choose to put one foot in front of the other and put action into place. it could be as simple as choosing to get caught up on the laundry one day, paying the bills and going through the piles of school paper on the kitchen counter the next day, or reaching out to friends! 
since i was feeling overwhelmed and in that funky place today i decided i needed to lean in to my incredible community! on a call earlier i shared what was on my heart and the struggles i was feeling! my incredible friends helped lift me up and give me the strength i needed to avoid crawling into that hole or avoiding everything today! i made a plan and decided to get my workout in! for me moving my body and breaking a sweat always gets my endorphins going and that always helps improve my mood. i also decided to take some action and get some things accomplished. i’ll be checking back in with my friends later to let them know i did what i said i was going to do.

i’m not sure if you can relate or if you struggle too, but know you’re not alone!

since i was feeling overwhelmed and in that funky place today i decided i needed to lean in to my incredible community! on a call earlier i shared what was on my hea and the struggles i was feeling! my incredible friends helped lift me up and give me the strength i needed to avoid crawling into that hole or avoiding everything today! i made a plan and decided to get my workout in! for me moving my body and breaking a sweat always gets my endorphins going and that always helps improve my mood. i also decided to take some action and get some things accomplished. i’ll be checking back in with my friends later to let them know i did what i said i was going to do.

i’m not sure if you can relate or if you struggle too, but know you’re not alone!

text: ok dv story #2  one year i went out of town with my sister tracy we wanted to visit my grandmothers grave site it’s strange i don’t even remember the details of that trip it’s all so vague but i blacked out a lot of past situations that recently came back to me but anyway we went and when we arrived back in the bay area she had to stop at the law office she worked for and pick up some paperwork to deliver somewhere i remember her office was in richmond at john burris law firm so needless to say we were late getting me home i knew he would have an issue and i was ready for it but it got crazy quick he accused me of lying and being with some other man nothing o said mattered he choked me through me on the bed stripped off all my clothes too off his belt and tied my hands and legs together behind me kinda like you would do cattle he kept me like that for over an hour yelling and screaming telling me to shut up i did this to myself i made him do this when he finally untied me he got his shot gun and said go ahead and call somebody i’ll shoot any muther f***er that comes into my house his brother was downstairs living with us at the time i heard him say come **** but still no one helped me that was the hardest thing the police never helped they would say you guys are married?  you guys work it out. my church would say pray for him god doesn’t like divorce my family?  i never told till years late because someone would have been dead if my uncle kelly knew #domesticviolence #domesticabuse #timesup #metoo #pdxpeople #pdxstories #survivor #abusesurvivor

text:
“the trump administration is planning to double down on “religious liberty” protections that could affect birth control access and allow for lgbtq employment discrimination.

planned rules would strengthen or expand existing religious liberty protections for employers to deny health care access or make hiring decisions based on their religious beliefs and “moral convictions.” the potential regulations continue the trump administration’s push for “religious liberty,” which president donald trump has emphasized through multiple executive orders protecting religious liberty. other executive branch agencies have also made their own moves to protect religious freedom, including the u.s. department of health and human services and department of justice.

the trump administration is pushing forward with its efforts to allow more employers to deny reproductive health coverage to their employees on the basis of their religious beliefs.

the department of health and human services sent a new rule to the white house office of management and budget on oct. 11, which would “expand exemptions to protect religious beliefs” for employers who are currently required to provide health care coverage for employees under the affordable care act. the rule would expand current protections for religious groups and “closely held” private companies who gained protections through the 2014 u.s. supreme court ruling in burwell v. hobby lobby stores.

this marks the second attempt by the trump administration to curtail birth control coverage. the administration previously issued a similar rule in 2017, which was ultimately blocked by the courts after multiple legal challenges.”
continued below ⬇️⬇️

text: real talk? it's been a tough week, or few weeks, maybe months, yes. but, there is joy in so much around us, i see it. i'm grateful to the folks who've reached out to check on me recently, but a lot of this current phase of healing requires that i tap into my personal sense of being, replenish my own reserves, and return once again to that precocious shoulder-shakin' little bird i have always been, step by step. i'm still here, working on me. you do the same for you, yes? ☮❤️ @tamar.salibian  #fbf february 2015 #throwback #hard #dance #move #rihanna #futurephd #healing #selfcare #selflove #metoo #believesurvivors #gratitude #flashback #selfworth #therapy #shouldershake #physicalfitness #emotionalfitness #solitude #thedancingscholar ✌🏻️ music: hard by rihanna. song is chopped & edited, copyright infringement not intended.

we all trust you and support you, stay strong 🙏
god bless you 🙏

text:
многие социально-политические движения начинают очень даже за здравие, а заканчивают - за упокой... рациональное, прогрессивное зерно без промедления берётся в оборот селекционерами от политики - обрабатывается всеми возможными гербицидами и, мутируя, вместо сильного, тянущегося к солнцу дерева выдаёт уродливую безжизненную деревяшку.
.
так набирающие силу народные движения выливаются в проплаченные из соросовских и прочих фондов оранжевые революции, после которых страна только номинально остаётся на карте. долго за примером ходить не надо...
.
так феминизм из волны свежего ветра и равенства возможностей вырождается в  мизандрические марши изрыгаюших ненависть розовых шапочек под предводительством мадонны.
.
так разумные требования прекратить гонения на лгбт... эюя трансформируются в агрессивную нормализацию любого рода квира, атаки на "оскорбительно архаичную" семью мама-папа-ребенок и психологическое, а нередко и физическое... калеченье детей гомосексуальной пропагандой
.
из этой же оперы -  набирающее разрушительную силу движение #metoo - задуманное, возможно, с благими намерениями (которыми вымощена дорога известно куда) как публичное раскрытие случаев сексуальных домогательств и изнасилований.
.
в 2015 г. актриса алиса милано (alyssa milano) выступила в твиттере с призывом раскрыть замалчиваемые случаи сексуального насилия. результат оказался непредвиденным: только в течение года хэштег подхватили 19 миллионов женщин. казалось бы, движение могло стать очистительной позитивной волной - но не тут-то было. как обычно, нашлись искусные (и состоятельные...) сценаристы, быстренько перекроившие план действий что называется на коленке
.
и сегодня мы имеем тысячи сфабрикованных обвинений и поломанных жизней. факты и доказательства здесь роли не играют, равно как и презумпция невиновности. мало того, нормальных людей уже так достал этот цирк, что, если даже с женщиной действительно случится беда, вряд ли ей уже поверят и встанут на её защиту - как в известной притче, где мальчик-пастушок часто без оснований кричал "спасите! волки!" - и в итоге, когда волки действительно двинулись на него из леса, никто уже не принял его крики за чистую монету.
.
#очемговорятвамерике
name: Once Upon a Time in America

text:
i did a thing and it was brave
.
this piece had my heart and soul and the response to it from everyone was very overwhelming and validating. i'm so proud of myself for exhibiting this piece. i needed the platform to tell my story.
.
i took the principal to this piece and said, 'you're the person i want to see this piece'. and i explained it to him. in detail. the piece is about my activism and experience of being a victim. it is about the reporting process. it is about my trauma. it is about 'holding space'for people's burden. it is about being a survivor.
.
i felt like that was a really symbolic way of ending off my year. reporting a teacher was me showing the truth. i showed the truth to the man who had power and was responsible to protect me. so, again, i took him to the artwork about that and showed him the truth. .
.
.
.
.

federal prosecutors are not naming the senators who received the threatening messages.

text:
work work work 💪

my full time career is selling complex technology solutions for large corporate tax departments. it's challenging because tax is confusing, practically impossible to automate and changes every year! i create simple solutions for complex problems and sell them via demonstrations and get my prospects excited about change!

the biggest issue with my clients however isn't anything technical.... their software implementations fail simply because they refuse to change. they go back to their familiar process of excel because it is easy and blame the technology rather then take personal responsibility for the issue. 
this is essentially the exact same thing i witnessed at treatment.  the therapy and tools provided work wonders when the individual actually wants to change and will follow the instructions but pretty much no one did. they said it was stupid or the therapy was useless but none of that is true at all, they simply didn't put in any effort to change. until people are really going to work on change daily nothing happens.... it's a waste of time and money, much like when people buy expensive software and then don't implement it correctly because of the pain of change 
the similarities between my struggles as a technical sales engineer and those of my therapists in treatment were actually quite similar and have helped me enormously in my career see the problem of addiction is literally everywhere. change is hard but certainly possible when we take the time to do it correctly!

my software career began in implementation so i have a ton of experience in implementing change correctly and used that skill set in treatment.  i came prepared to learn and from day one listened and took the advice of the therapists even when it involved doing incredibly uncomfortable things. all their advice changed my life forever 💓 @passagesmalibu 
#godry #drydiet #godry #healthyandwealthy #addictionrecovery #onedayatatime #recoveroutloud #sober #weightlossjourney #transformation #empoweringwomen #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth

text:
you know what’s worse than facing something scary? facing it alone. 
you may say that you’re a “private” person, or that your healing must be done by yourself, but in my experience healing happens quicker, with deeper, lasting results when we come together in community 
so i want to host a live, virtual workshop next week to go deeper with what we started with permission to speak from your heart. everyone will have a chance to share, if they want, and depending on numbers i may be able to pull a card for everyone on the call. 
if you have not joined the private group, i encourage you do so, this way you are also recieving the juicy content for your trauma recovery 
the link is at the top of the page 🔝🔝🔝🔝
you will find it in my bio!

text:
heroes are what keeps life going. our first hero is that person who made the choice of carrrying you for about nine months. 👶🏾
.

think about it, have you ever carried anything physical for nine months? but that's what heroes do! we just call that first on a heroine. 👩🏾
.

so if they can build families, protect their young, nurture a nation, build empires, and stabilize chaotic situations like our economy, why not run the country? 🇺🇸
.
right now there is a war on our heroines. let's do what we can do to empower them, and protect them.
. 👱‍♀️👷🏽‍♀️👧🏾👩🏽‍⚕️👩🏼👩🏽‍🎓👩‍🌾👩🏻‍🏫👩🏿‍💼👩‍🔬👵👵🏾👩🏾‍🚀👸🏿🕵️‍♀️👩‍✈️

text:
האם את מרגישה ‏מתוסכלת כשאת מסתכלת במראה?
האם ‏זה עצר אותך בחיים? אל תתני לזה להיות! ‏בואי לגלות את עצמך מחדש דרך סשן צילום טיפולי! המפגש עם המצלמה מאפשר לך לראות את ‏עצמך ‏דרך עיניי ‏המתבונן. זה ‏מלמד אותך איך להוציא את היופי הפנימי החוצה ‏ומחזק את הביטחון העצמי לך. ‏מאות נשים כבר ‏‏גילו את החוויה ‏המתכנת הזו ויוצאות ממנה מאוהבות בעצמן. תלמדי להסתכל על עצמך בעין אחרת ‏ותשני את החיים שלך ‏לטובה. ‏לאהוב את עצמך הוא הבסיס של ‏חיים מאושרים.

please share this guys and support those who are not wrong and don't believe anything that is being shared without knowing the truth .

text_retweet:
#repost @theebutterflyproject
・・・
black women are deemed overbearing, having bad attitudes,  disrespectful and so much more. alongside, that we are the least paid in  the hierarchy. this stat is disheartening because with everything  against us, we are the most battered. the reason we are like this is  because we have hard fights at home where we don't get to be strong and  powerful at home. submission is pushed in black homes. as we submit we  often settle. all women are to be loved, cherished and protected. the  black woman is desiring that same feeling. next time you see a black  woman that seems as if she is carrying a heavy load, encourage her. it's  possible she's been abused physically, mentally, financially or any  other way and needs the support.
.

text: so we made a call to action film about homeless women in america, how women are the fastest growing group to lose their homes and how 85% of women are raped on the streets.. i asked the ladies what they wanted to say and they said that as homeless women they are judged and ignored and so we decided to build a feminine safe space for the women to tell their stories.. we got lots of clothes which the women kept and they dressed showered and looked how they would if they didn’t lose their homes. the film shows how it can really happen to anyone.. last tuesday i managed to gather the women from their tents all over los angeles to give them a screening, everyone cried and laughed and they left with hope! these are some of our women at the screening, some of the ladies weren’t anywhere to be found. i’m looking to find a home for the film but in the meantime please check out our wonderful website where you can donate to shelters.. www.helphouseher.org.. please dm if you want to get involved.. and #mayagrams built the website.. female filmmaker friday: behind the scenes shooting our film ‘her too’ #filmmakerfridays #femalefilmmakerfriday #femalefilmmaker #filmmaker #documentaryfilm #documentaryfilmmaking #documentaryfilmmaker  #auteur #auteurfilmmaker #auterfilmmaking #losangeles #homelessness #homelessnessawareness #socialactivism #socialactivist #calltoaction #calltoactionfilm #womeninfilmandtv #metoo #metoomovement #hellosunshine #knucklehead #freethebid #noustousgallery #sunsetedit #themill #annetrotman

text:
i wrote this piece about the #metoo movement. as i say in the blog:
.
.
.
i waited to say these things until the political circus of the kavanaugh hearings were over, until harvey weinstein wasn't the token face of the male violator allowing other men to hide in his very large shadow. and though there is a culture of rape, a culture of misogynism that must be urgently addressed by all of us, right now this is about a #metoo movement of sexual assault survivors, their stories, their demands. it's about shutting up and listening. it's not about men being heard, we've always been heard. right now it is about our sisters speaking and men not speaking over them.
.
.
.
the words that follow are to my brothers. in case they need a little clarity, a little context for the #metoo movement. i wrote this because i love my brothers but i am also angry. because any society that protects the powerful and marginalizes victims is an affront to all things good and decent. i hope everyone will read these words, take them to heart, share them virally. i want the world to be safe for my sisters. i want their voices to be heard. link in bio. xoxo
.
.
.
#biblicalchristianity #women #men #sexualassault #metoo #genderequality #harveyweinstein #politics

text:

text:
{{ my body is not a public space }}
⠀⠀
to the guy who thought it was acceptable to harass me on my way to ytt, grab me and grope my arse and crotch...it’s not funny, it’s not a game, it’s sexual harassment and a complete violation of a woman’s space
⠀⠀
thanks to you, i didn’t leave my house for 4 days and completely withdrew. me running did not mean chase me, it meant i was scared of what you would do to me. me saying no when you tried to touch me was not an invitation to try harder
⠀⠀
for the record i was wearing a baggy yoga jumpsuit at the time, but i could have been wearing a bikini and you still would not have had the right to touch me. this type of behaviour is not as uncommon as people may think, but it is 100% unacceptable and it needs to stop!!
⠀⠀

the things we transcend- 
7/9 works titled “the things we create” each piece is based on ideas we create and see as reality. our thoughts become our truth. while some are negative and some are positive they all manifest in the creation of who we think we are. inspired while listening to the philosophies of alan watts on #audiblebooks and while contemplating the realities that women are facing today in america and have always faced all over the world. .
.
.

minister of state (mos) for external affairs, m. j. akbar on monday filed a defamation case in delhi’s patiala house court against priya ramani, the journalist who alleged that akbar sexually harassed her.

a statement from akbar’s lawyers confirmed that the complaint has been filed under sections 499 and 500 of the indian penal code.

akbar has been facing flak over the allegations, with opposition parties demanding the minister’s resignation.

however, the bharatiya janata party (bjp) leader on sunday did not indicate any decision to step down and said that he will take a legal recourse in the matter.

reacting to legal  action from bjp minister  ramani’s statement came hours after akbar filed a criminal defamation case against her at a delhi court and around the same time one more woman came forward with a #metoo story about mj akbar (more on that later). “truth and the absolute truth is my only defence,” ramani said in her statement as she criticised akbar for attempting to silence women through “intimidation and harassment”. responding to the defamation case, a host of twitterati promised to crowd source a fund to back priya ramani and other accusers. 
in october last year, when the #metoo campaign peaked in hollywood, journalist priya ramani had written an article for vogue india, titled, “to the harvey weinstein of the world” and narrated her ordeal about the gut-wrenching incident of sexual misconduct she faced during a job interview with a renowned journalist who had “transformed indian journalism”.akbar, who on sunday returned from an official trip to nigeria, issued a statement, denying all allegations as “wild and baseless.” “ms priya ramani began this campaign a year ago with a magazine article. she did not however name me as she knew it was an incorrect story. when asked recently why she had not named me, she replied, in a tweet: ‘never named him because he didn’t ‘do’ anything.’ https://splco.me/eng/2018/10/15/twitterati-support-priya-ramanis-with-crowd-fund-to-take-on-m-j-akbar/

#akbar #bjp #crowdfund #metoo

sunday 10/21 at 2:30pm: word up community bookshop is pleased to host nelly rosario, author of songs of the water saints, in conversation with local author john paul infante @infantejp. nelly and john will discuss brooklyn, santo domingo, texas state university, engineering at mit, columbia university, songs of the water saints, fuckboys, #metoo, the words: “dique,” “pariguayo,” and “tecato”—or they might talk something completely different—join us to find out. p.s.: they will definitely discuss sancocho. that much is certain. this conversation is presented by dominican writers - please search for "nelly rosario" on eventbrite to register for this free event. 💙💙💙💙💙

text:
historically, as women in south asian families, we have seen gender bias evolve in our time. as south asian women today, we are just as empowered in some cases as previous generations but today we believe we have more of a ‘tribe’ that elevates and supports us in all that we do as moms and women.

at at time when #metoo and #timesup movements are mobilizing women around the world, there is more momentum than ever to make your voice heard and help those who have been silent, to find their voices and make a change when it comes to gender parity, domestic abuse, violence against women and sexual harassment–all things we have seen in our communities too.  we are arming the next generation with tools to do just that. as we go forward in our journeys through motherhood it’s important to remember the strides we as mothers have made and also the gaps that remain. recently we talked to to 10 moms about the strides we have made and challenges that remain. what are your thoughts? how are south asian women making progress? we will build on this series in the next few months, stay tuned! #womenwholead #women #raisinggirls #masalamommas

text:
ruby rumie's monumental wall of portraits lugar común positions the relationship between women across class-divides in colombia by stripping the sitters of jewelry and fashion which might otherwise announce socio-economic status. these portraits serve as a way of visualizing the often unacknowledged intimate relationships and connections between women who clean, work and live in the same household.

last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.

fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation.

where students were gathered and actively participated in the session.

the session was about topics that included:
🔸voice of women

🔸speech on #metoo

text:
#winning #gotem #howitsdone — #donaldtrump was greeted with cheers from supporters on the ground at a campaign stop in missoula, #montana on thursday. from the air, however, he may have spotted a different kind of welcome.
-
protesters transformed some local landmarks into anti-trump messages, with “liar” and “impeach” visible from the air ― and potentially from air force one, if the president happened to glance out the window.
-
#mountjumbo, which overlooks the city, already had an “l” on it for the nearby loyola sacred heart catholic high school. protesters simply added three more letters in honor of the president’s arrival:
-
mount sentinel also received a modification. the “m” atop that peak was adorned with some extra letters to spell “impeach.”
-
although #trump won montana by 20 points in 2016, the rally on thursday night was held in missoula, one of a half-dozen counties in the state that voted for hillary clinton.
—

text:
trigger ⚠️ warning: sexual violence, gender-based violence, domestic violence. 
do you like horror movies? ever notice how violence against women is sometimes normalized in the films? also how the sexualization fo female characters is emphasized?

join rsvp as we explore the role of violence against women (vaw) in horror films and how the horror film industry capitalizes on vaw as a horror plot ploy. how can we imagine the horror film genre shifting in the current era of #metoo? 
our intention with this event is to not only validate the experiences of survivors and how horror films can be triggering for many in our communities but to also imagine how horror films can and are shifting in today's era of the #metoomvmt.

we're pleased to host this event in conversation with professor lan duong, associate professor in cinema & media studies at the university of southern california. her research interests include feminist film theory, postcolonial literature, and asian/american film and literature. duong’s critical works can be found in signs, melus, journal of southeast asian studies, journal of asian american studies, inter-asia cultural studies, amerasia, asian cinema, discourse, velvet light trap, and the anthologies, transnational feminism in film and media, southeast asian cinema, recollecting vietnam, and gendering the transpacific. link in bio!

please read this entire post. the current conservative government has decided to disband the violence against women roundtable which was started in 2015 to provide strategic advice to the government on emerging issues related to violence against women. this roundtable was led and informed by incredible educators like farrah khan pamela cross and sly castaldi .they worked tirelessly on bills like #148,  a bill that gave 5 days paid leave for survivors and ensured that workplaces worked towards equity and safety in a time when we need this the most. 
currently, mpp lisa macleod and the conservative government have done the following damage to women and survivors in ontario: - cancelled sexual health education
- want to re open to abortion debate
- cancelled bill #148
- disbanded the vaw rountable
- froze the minimum wage - cancelled funding and support to sis and ops - funneled more money to toronto police from mental health services
- and now are threatening to pull funding from life saving organizations that support survivors, their families, their communities and work to end sexual violence and gbv.

we are at a critical time when working together as close as we can is crucial to fighting the austerity and oppression of our current government. more than ever, survivors, allies and community leaders must work together to resist the damage and danger we face. violence against women in ontario has reached a crisis state. as farrah khan had stated "according to canadian femicide observatory, 50% of the femicides in canada this year were in ontario. 53 women have died due to femicide in this province from jan-august. this is a crisis.demand for sexual assault services increases as awareness increases. in 2016, there were 50,000 calls to sexual assault crisis lines in ontario. these requests have increased in the wake of high-profile cases of sexual violence and the rise of the #metoo and #timesup movements." use this hashtag #survivorscantwait and resist these cuts and changes with us.

text:
on fridays, i wear black in solidarity with my sisters and other womxn who still feel like they haven’t found their voices, for personal, societal, or fear based reasons. i see you. i have been you. and now, i am tapping deep into my sacred feminine and sacred rage and saying “yes” to all that arises, because i’ve said “no” or “not right now” for too long.
>>>
i do not need to be ashamed of the stories that once haunted me. i did not deserve the interactions and experiences that at a young age, wired the neuro-pathways in my brain to believe that i am unlovable, broken, not enough. i can not hold my body hostage against toxic masculinity any longer. i will not stay silent in the darkness when there is healing and freedom to be had.
>>>
the #blackfridays call to action this week said, “to all who are grieving for themselves and this country, who are in pain and feeling the deep effects of this toxic culture—some for the first time, and others, as they have for their entire lifetimes--you are not alone.” and i realized, as those words sank into my body, that for the first time in a long time, i do not feel alone. i have been getting really fucking uncomfortable and reaching out and posting and sharing and guess what? i am not alone. and neither are you. and it feels really good to realize that what once only lived in the shadows not only can, but has every right to be shared, to be released, and to be healed, in whatever that looks like for your own journey. and that the support is abundantly here.
>>>
i am here. others are here. just reach out. get involved. go to the link in my bio if you want to receive the weekly calls to action. come to tonight’s cacao ceremony and join me and 15 or so humans in divine connection and the medicine that we can only receive when we are seen and heard and have the freedom to feel fully.

text:
it has been a tough week but lmao it’s nothing compared to the next week. 
it’s simple i’ve an appointment every single day. but i’m well surrounded in this trial ( don’t know the good translation?) . thursday will be the hardest; i’m gonna meet my advocate to establish my speech for the complaint. to file this complaint will be fuckin hard to me. im feeling so fucking fragile at this moment. i hope that the victim’s words gonna be released and that those motherfuckers will pay accordingly with their actions. 
pour être franche j’ai peur de déterrer des émotions que j’avais bien cachées, dans des tiroirs fermés à double tour 🔐 . j’ai peur de ce tsunami 🌊 que je vais me prendre dans la gueule. j’ai l’habitude de verrouiller mes émotions en bonne #borderline que je suis parce que j’en ai putain de peur. je ne veux pas me rappeler de cette période au fond de moi. mais j’irai jusqu’au bout. 
maman m’a dit merci ce matin. merci parce qu’elle aussi , en a marre de voir sa fille se traîner des boulets à chaque pied sans être reconnue de puis presque deux décennies. et on en a chié toutes les deux. chacune a sa manière. mais toujours liées dans l’enfer de la maladie 😷. je veux tourner cette page. je veux l’inscrire sur cette putain de plainte et la brûler a jamais. 
je fais pas ça pour me venger, avec cette putain de justice française je serais bien incapable de me rassasier de la peine ( s’il est déclaré coupable) qu’il va se prendre. 
je le fais pour moi. changer mon rapport aux hommes, à mon corps sali et complètement bousillé, à ma sexualité en vrac, je le fais pour ma famille, pour cette maman qui en a fait des insomnies pendant que j’étais fourrée tous les trois jours en hp ou aux urgences. pour mon père aussi, qui a été je le regrette mis à l’écart et qui n’a pas toujours compris ma détresse. mais je le fais avant tout pour avancer. et plus j’y pense, plus je me sens vaillante et vaindicative. je vais tout niquer. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
#mentalhealth #bpd#ptsd#rapesurvivor #metoo#rapevictim#survivor#recovery#ootd#outfit #outfitoftheday #softgrunge#grunge#grungestyle#frenchie#look#grungeaesthetic#aesthetic#triples#endofrapeculture

text:
it’s friday! and it’s been a while... so let’s do a #fridayintroduction!

i’m taylor! a 24 year old wife, mother, daughter, sister, friend, leader, and jesus lover. 
i’m a big fan of anything chocolate, coffee, or fresh. i long for cool days where i can wear jeans, t-shirt, and a cardigan all day. i love the rain, especially when i can open up all of my windows and clean while it’s pouring outside. i think animals know us + the world better than we do, and i believe my dog is the most intuitive person i know. 
lately, i’ve been struggling a lot with what’s going on in the news. i’m not a super political person, but sometimes there are times you have to speak up and have an opinion. i believe we need to support women, trust women, listen to women, and #believewomen. 
i’ve gone through my own stories of harassment and assault, and i pray for a day that that isn’t the norm anymore. i pray for a day when a woman telling me they’ve been hurt is a shock and not a slight head nod with the response #metoo. 
i also pray for the day that we as a nation can recognize and acknowledge that it happens, it’s wrong, and it should be made right. i pray that women find the strength to move past their story and are able to say “this was done to me, but my worth does not lie in it”. what types of things really ruffle your feathers in society? what are you passionate about abolishing or bringing more light to? let that drive your conversations, your career, your relationships. and please, please get out and vote. ❤️

text:
2/5 - halloween (2018)
director: david gordon green
-
"michael myers let loose on halloween night?" asks one character in david gordon green's lifeless remake of john carpenter's masterpiece, before continuing, "what are we gonna do? cancel halloween?" well...yeah. green and co have gone out of their way to stress that we're supposed to pretend the other sequels never happened, like we're supposed to forget we've seen this same movie, note for note, eight other times, each one more derivative than the last. but in the end, being referential isn't a crime. what is a crime is green's complete lack of understanding of what makes a functional slasher, as well as what made the original film great. as a director, he's a genre chameleon, going for stoner comedy in 'pineapple express' one minute and inspirational biopic 'stronger' in the next. because green never stays long enough in one lane to perfect his craft, his quality is similarly all over the place. 'halloween,' with it's misplaced priorities, is a prime example. here's a list of things green doesn't understand about 'halloween': 1) carpenter's film exuded a thick menace that relied on the atmosphere of dread and the inevitable, while green's film is almost solely focused on gruesome kills (uncharacteristic of 1978 myers) and money shots. filming myers as if he was a badass action hero to be admired (as one terrible shot of him closing a car trunk does) makes it virtually impossible for green to recover any sense of menice that might have been. 2) the script, which somehow took three people to write, is far more focused on winking asides like the one that began this review than creating anything that resembles a relatable human being. the pain inflicted on pros like jamie lee curtis and judy greer (great actors giving terrible performances) by these scribes is far worse than anything myers ends up doing.  3) the tacked on #metoo ending feels forced and unearned at best, cynical at worst. 'halloween' circa 2018 is a painfully dour affair; and in a year that gave us emotionally resonant rule breakers like 'hereditary' and 'the quiet place,' that simply is unacceptable.

text: medusa was not a monster. i used to think so, until i learned her story from a female perspective. to paraphrase, athena protected medusa by giving her the power to make any man who looked at her completely harmless. the popular stories we are taught have gone through a filter of gender biases, not to mention race and class. medusa was raped, betrayed, hunted down, had her children stolen from her and was then killed and used as a weapon to glorify the people who did these things to her in the first place. medusa is an icon and symbol for women, but like so women many after her, she was made out to be a monster. #metoo #powertomedusa #uffizigallery #florence ✊🏻🐍 #medusa

text:
i was honored to serve as a judge today for a high school competition in western new york where students presented on gender in the media in the age of #metoo

one student interviewed her teacher about her personal experiences with the gender pay gap. another profiled a female sports tv journalist who spoke about barriers to entry in reporting on sports. a group of student filmmakers produced a three-part series on date rape at high school parties. another student wrote about the lack of representation of native american women in the media.

this photo was part of a series of photos that focuses on the difficulties sexual assault survivors face. "the female’s eyes are covered because she is blinded by the fear of telling someone what has happened to her." (photo credit: salamanca high school students)

i'm excited to see how this next generation of media makers will change the narrative. 
to quote one of the student's op-eds: "women everywhere should be prepared, because the revolution is just getting started."

text:
"🕺jest piąteczek, wchodzisz do klubu i jakiś ziomek oblizuje się na twój widok… 🌭🌭znacie to? uporczywe wlepianie wzroku, niby przypadkiem dotknięcie tyłka 😤😤😤" (via @januszek.official )
pamiętam jak zaczęła się akcja #metoo i ludzie pisali: ale co to da, że każda laska coś napisze w necie. mi dużo dało to, że dziewczyny pisały o swoich doświadczeniach. po pierwsze zobaczyłam skalę problemu, po drugie poczułam niesamowitą solidarność i odwagę wśród dziewczyn, po trzecie zobaczyłam, że jest inne wyjście niż dołączenie do klubu dystans. że moim jedynym wyjściem kiedy jadę w tramwaju i koleś siedząc naprzeciwko mnie lustruje ostentacyjnie moje nogi w rajstopkach, wlepia we mnie wzrok i traktuje jak śliczne mięsko nie jest udawanie, że tego nie widzę, że mnie to nie rusza i mam dystans. tu jest miejsce na moja reakcję i uświadomienie tej osobie, że to już nie są lata 90 i kobiety nie będą udawać, że tego uprzedmiotawiania nie widzą albo uznawać cmokanie i gwizdanie na ulicy za komplement (nie jestem psem!!). idę za radami m.in. @princessnokia i kiedy jestem w stanie to zwracam tym osobom uwagę. często wystarczy zatrzymanie się i spojrzenie prosto w oczy - zwykle już są spłoszeni, zdarzało mi się podchodzić i pytać "o co chodzi? czy jest jakiś problem, że tak na mnie ciągle patrzy w dziwny sposób?". kiedy obok mnie jest #menspreading robię na to #womanspreading reakcja to zwykle spojrzenie, prychnięcie i nie zawłaszczanie dłużej mojej przestrzeni. nie bójmy się mówić nie kiedy coś nam się nie podoba! 💕💕💕💕💕💕💕💕💕💕💕

text:
you don’t want to miss this wonderful event @gibneydance has put together:
during #domesticviolenceawarenessmonth, leaders in the arts and social justice will come together to advance the conversation about the #metoo movement and where it might be headed. we will discuss the diverse roles artists, journalists and lawyers play in this movement as well as ways that different sectors of action can unite to strengthen #metoo and move it forward.
⠀
speakers will include:
• qurrat ann kadwani, award-winning actress, producer, mc, tv host and philanthropist
• robin pogrebin, new york times reporter
• our very own andrew sta. ana, director of legal services here @dayoneny!
the breakfast will be moderated by kayhan irani, emmy award-winning writer and cultural activist.
⠀
tickets are offered on a sliding scale (#linkinbio to purchase) and will support gibney’s community action initiatives that use art as a means to prevent and move beyond violence 365 days a year.
⠀
note: this is not a media event, though members of the media will be present.
original photo: copyright gina gibney dance inc., photo by scott shaw.

the goddess has many names, just like the women in this country do. this dassehra may our women draw from her grace, her shakti, her strength, her compassion and be one with her. yes, look within, unite with your goddess within you and say #metoo to give it a whole new meaning.  in a country where the mother reigns supreme, may our men learn to apply that value in real time, so there is no more wrong, injustice, hypocrisy, agony, humiliation, stress, discomfort, pain or suffering, no more me too for womankind. may we all unite solemnly, equally, as one and stand with each other, with dignity and respect. may there be peace, love, empathy, acceptance and patience within all our hearts. 
may our goodness triumph over evil, wisdom over ignorance balance over prejudice, equality over chaivinism, questions over easy assumed judgements. after all, the purpose of these auspicious days or the stories of ram or durga, is not to settle for answers but to look inward and ask questions on our own thoughts and actions that provide us a pure unadulterated conscience and wellbeing for all.

wish you all a shubh dassehra and shubho bijoya!

text:
sam: folk (people) in those stories had lots of chances of turning back, only they didn't. they kept going... because they were holding on to something.

frodo: what are we holding on to, sam?

sam: that there's some good in this world, mr. frodo. and it's worth fighting for! – frodo and sam, from the lord of the rings: the two towers. 
around the world, everyday, people are making the choice to keep going, as they are compelled by their belief that their cause - climate change, equal rights, clean air & water, hunger, tyranny, metoo, and countless others - is worth fighting for. more power to those fighting the good fight.

have a good weekend!

wish you all a shubh dassehra and shubho bijoya!

please choose tasty meat free alternatives and help stop hell on earth for animals.

text:
good afternoon! 
check out the summary from last night! it was great to meet such inspirational women! 
thank you to @newberry_college for hosting an amazing panel discussion on the #metoo movement. the panel discussion explored resources and challenges endured by women, femmes, and trans people in south carolina. the alumni music center was filled! every seat was taken and some guests had to sit on the floor. it was amazing to see such a diverse group of people. 
the panelists chosen were excellent resources and advocates on these issues. 
kathleen hayes spoke on behalf of the indigenous women’s alliance of sc. she spoke on how important it is for south carolina to have “native american” listed on police reports. we need the data to help our sisters. she also talked about accountability of ones actions. she believes community is just as important today as it has traditionally been in native culture. by having a community we hold each other accountable for our actions. 
#mmiw was talked about by kathleen because like the #metoo movement it has helped women come forward to talk about their abuse and to seek help. both movements are helping native women to come forward and tell their story. 
we look forward to being invited to more panels to discuss native issues. having a voice for those who can’t is so important right now, especially for native women. last night we heard of many resources in our state to help women who suffer from sexual abuse. please reach out if you need help! we are here to guide you to get the help you need. 
thanks to other amazing panelists:
@crawfordeme with @wrenetwork 
@queerwomxnist with @centerforsocialequity 
vivian anderson with @everyblackgirl 
@meeghankane with @unsweetenedmag 
#southcarolina #southcarolinaevents #panel #womensrights #womensupportingwomen #makeanimpact #mmiw #nativeamerican #nativewomen #nativerights #indigenous #womenempowerment #womenrightsactivist

text:
sharing looks on instagram was very scary to me! 😢 for 1, i was afraid people wouldn't like me or support my ideas. and for 2, i was afraid to show myself. i finally took a risk to openly express myself, and i have received support all over the world. 😍 when you believe in yourself, others will appreciate it. makeup to me isn't just about beauty. it's channeling my creative energy into something that may inspire others. it's about overcoming my insecurities, my depression and anxiety, and allowing the passion inside of me to be uninhibited. i will be more consistent for my next 100 posts. i'll also show my other talents more often. and hopefully you'll be here to see it. thank you! 🖤
.

text:
challenge 107: redesign refresher: the tragedy of deforestation .
.
this idea was originally drawn to visually represent the feeling of feeling stuck and heartbroken. i have to admit…this one was a hard one for me to re-do since it had so much meaning behind it. the hollow feeling in one’s heart isn’t something easy to overcome. this is why i wanted to give one of my favorite sketches another life, but this time to represent the heartbreak of deforestation and what it does to our environment. many animals, birds, plants, reptiles, amphibians, insects all call the rainforest home, yet we as humans constantly take their land and use their homes and resources either as land for (more) ranches, farms and urban use. other uses include timber used for fuel (coal) or building. these lands then turn into inhabitable wastelands and more and more of them are being created as more and more species of all the above continue to decline into extinction. this is the heartbreaking truth and i hope that my illustration portrays that feeling justly. we all need to do better. 🌳🌲🌴🙏🏻🌱🌎🌍🌏✨🍃
.
.

to check out more of my artwork please visit my art of where and redbubble shops, and make sure to follow my work on facebook! links in bio❤️ if you really like this illustration and would like to license my illustrations or represent me as a illustrator or designer please inbox me for rates and collaboration opportunities! id love to hear from you! 🙏🏻👩‍🎨

text:
as i sit in my cold ny studio apartment and having vacation withdrawals - i know it was time to come back because there is very important work to be done. but friends, i need your help...well, actually, we need your help. did you know that in 2017, 83.2% of artists in popular content were men and only 16.8% were women? and of the 2,767 credited songwriters, only 12.3% were female. pretty wild, right?  @womencrushmusic has put on over 85 events across 13 cities internationally in the last year to create opportunities for rising women songwriters and hopefully be able to shift those statistics. we only have a few days left to raise 10k to help us continue connecting, educating and inspiring women in music in the us, canada, and hopefully soon across the world. 
share the campaign, donate if you can. we appreciate you. <3
link: bit.ly/keepcrushin
(also in bio)

today as we celebrate dusshera, a festival which is symbol of victory of good over evil; i think to myself why do we burn ravan every year, are we really killing the evil??
on one hand we are experiencing phenomenal growth in terms of technology and science, businesses like ott (over the top) are on boom in india and on the other hand we still need movements such as #metoo for our women to speak up for their basic rights.
to begin with, we have to deal with some major social issues on priority. these are the issues which have the power to pull back the progress of our country and by evolving our mentality slightly we can actually make a huge difference. let’s start removing the below evils from our society :
shaming
air, sound and water pollution
female infanticide
women unsafety
there are still a number of other social evils such as illiteracy, malnutrition, access to healthcare,  unsanitary conditions, wastage of food and corruption. honestly i can list many more.
how about we burn an evil every year instead of burning ravan?? i would say that’s sluggish but still a gradual progress. 
#happydusshera •

text_retweet:
one year ago, the movement #metoo, though not new, knew an international success (if one can call success the speaking up of thousands of women denouncing sexual harassment in all possible forms and contexts) and seemed to shake our societies out of their comfort bubble and the idea that we, naive women, constantly misinterpret men’s actions.
~
in france, a year and a half ago, this horrendous figure came out: 100% of women confirmed having been sexually harassed at least once in their lives.
~
yet it is an understatement to say that france’s response to #metoo is shameful. 100 wealthy and white women signed an open letter in which they claimed their “right to be importuned”. you read their sickening sentence right. in france, they take pride of two contradictory exceptions: french gallantry and french bawdiness. for these two preposterous reasons, we shouldn’t ask men to stop catcalling or harassing us.
~
but ain’t i a woman?! on that body which for once i show on my grid, isn’t there a head, a thinking head? under that short and sexy dress, isn’t there a feeling heart? my body and my pussy are mine, not yours! and if i chose bell hooks’ book to illustrate my anger, it’s also because white women throughout history have been complicit of the sexual aggressions of black women, and this cannot continue. feminism must be intersectional. it cannot recreate another form of oppression when it is fighting one. social advancement is social when it includes everyone.
~
so today i speak up to claim my body as mine and to be able to wear that short and sexy dress without fear of being raped in a dark alley. i speak up for all the women who are oppressed around the world by the heavy weights of sexism, racism, islamophobia, homophobia... our bodies, our decisions. 
ours. not yours. 
#speakupoctober #speakupphotochallenge
.
ps: i am posting this just after having had a violent row with an anti-abortion activist in front of the uni and to say that i am upset is an understatement. my body. my choice. not yours. not society’s.
——
#nonfiction #readwomen #feminism #bellhooks #aintiawoman

text:
for those of you new to my page.. hey! 🙋🏾‍♀️💕.. thank you for joining me here at the grown woman. you discovered my page probably due to my black history series. once it’s finished i’ll be back to sharing my words centered around self discovery, self acceptance and self love but always with room for real conversations on current affairs 😉. at 39 i’m still very much on my journey but it’s so much more fun journeying with like minded grown women. i want self love to go viral, beyond hashtags and cleverly worded captions and staged photos, i want it to grow roots deep within your heart and then spread like wild fire over everyone around you. .
.
this space is safe. it’s honest. it’s for all women (and men). i love to hear your stories and opinions so comment away whenever you feel the urge! .
.
ps. i’m a wife, mum of four, step mum of one and a londoner! ❤️
.
.
much love ... v xx

text:
👉भारत में चर्च कितना ताकतवर है, चर्च किस प्रकार मीडिया, बुद्धिजीवियों, नेताओं, अदालतों को कण्ट्रोल करता है, 👉बलात्कारी पादरी फ्रांको मुलाक्कल का केस इसका एक उदाहरण है, 👉अभी गुरुग्राम में ही चर्च एक जज और उसके परिवार को धर्मान्तरित करने में लगा था, 👉जज के परिवार ने धर्मान्तरित होने से मना किया वो धर्मान्तरित गार्ड महिपाल से उसके परिवार को गोलियां मरवा दी गयी😡 👉जालन्धर में बलात्कार के आरोपी बिशप का हीरो की तरह भव्य स्वागत, सभ्य समाज के मुंह पर तमाचा
👉केरल नन रेप केस में केरल हाईकोर्ट से जमानत मिलने के बाद बुधवार को बलात्कार का आरोपी बिशप फ्रैंको मुलक्कल के जालंधर पहुँचने के बाद बेहद शर्मनाक तरीके से उसका स्वागत किया गया। 👉बता दें कि केरल हाईकोर्ट ने सोमवार को इस बलात्कारी बिशप फ्रैंको मुलक्कल को रिहा करने का आदेश दिया था और यह मंगलवार को ही केरल के कोट्टायम जेल से रिहा हुआ हैं। 👉गौरतलब है कि जालंधर में जुलाई महीने में नन ने जालंधर के बिशप फ्रैंको मुलक्कल के खिलाफ रेप और शारीरिक उत्पीड़न की शिकायत दर्ज कराई थी। आरोपों के अनुसार, आरोपी बिशप को काम के सिलसिले में अक्सर केरल आना होता था। इस दौरान उसने कई बार नन के साथ रेप की वारदात को अंजाम दिया। 👉एक रेप के आरोपी बिशप का जिसे वेटिकन ने भी उसके पद से हटा दिया हो ऐसा जोरदार स्वागत देखना देश की हर महिला को पीड़ा पहुंचाने जैसा हैं। 👉आखिर हम एक समाज के तौर पर किस तरफ जाना चाहते हैं? कैसा समाज और माहौल हम अपनी आने वाली पीढ़ियों के लिए छोड़ना चाहते हैं? 👉जिस देश मे बलात्कारियों का इतना भव्य स्वागत होगा क्या उस समाज में यह नैतिक साहस बचेगा की वह अपनी स्त्रियों के सम्मान के लिए खड़ा हो सके? 👉बहरहाल यह शर्मनाक घटना बताती हैं कि हम न्याय के नाम पर सिर्फ रेप पीड़ित महिलाओं के लिए मोमबत्ती ही जला सकते हैं, 👉इसके अलावा कुछ नही कर सकते। 👉 देश मे एक तरफ #metoo अभियान चल रहा और ऐसे समय रेप जैसे गम्भीर आरोप के मुजरिम का इस तरह जमानत पाना और उसका इस तरह से फूलमालाओं के साथ भव्य स्वागत इस पूरे मुहिम को तगड़े झटके की तरह है। 👉आपको याद होगा की जम्मू के कठुआ कांड में जब लोग सीबीआई जांच की माँग को ले कर सड़क पर उतरे थे तो उन्हें देश के वामपंथी धड़े ने ‘बलात्कारी’ बताया था। 👉यहाँ तक की खुद को बुद्धिजीवी कहने वाली लेफ्ट लिबरल जमात, और बॉलीवुड की कुछ अभिनेत्रियां हाथो में प्लेकार्ड लेकर ‘देवी-स्थान’ ‘हिन्दू’ जैसे शब्दों के साथ ट्विटर पर उतर गई थी लेकिन अब इस रेप के आरोपी बिशप पर सभी लोगो ने मुंह मे दही जमा रखी हैं 😡
name: कट्टर हिन्दू सुनीता
tweet_full:
👉भारत में चर्च कितना ताकतवर है, चर्च किस प्रकार मीडिया, बुद्धिजीवियों, नेताओं, अदालतों को कण्ट्रोल करता है, 👉बलात्कारी पादरी फ्रांको मुलाक्कल का केस इसका एक उदाहरण है, 👉अभी गुरुग्राम में ही चर्च एक जज और उसके परिवार को धर्मान्तरित करने में लगा था, 👉जज के परिवार ने धर्मान्तरित होने से मना किया वो धर्मान्तरित गार्ड महिपाल से उसके परिवार को गोलियां मरवा दी गयी😡 👉जालन्धर में बलात्कार के आरोपी बिशप का हीरो की तरह भव्य स्वागत, सभ्य समाज के मुंह पर तमाचा
👉केरल नन रेप केस में केरल हाईकोर्ट से जमानत मिलने के बाद बुधवार को बलात्कार का आरोपी बिशप फ्रैंको मुलक्कल के जालंधर पहुँचने के बाद बेहद शर्मनाक तरीके से उसका स्वागत किया गया। 👉बता दें कि केरल हाईकोर्ट ने सोमवार को इस बलात्कारी बिशप फ्रैंको मुलक्कल को रिहा करने का आदेश दिया था और यह मंगलवार को ही केरल के कोट्टायम जेल से रिहा हुआ हैं। 👉गौरतलब है कि जालंधर में जुलाई महीने में नन ने जालंधर के बिशप फ्रैंको मुलक्कल के खिलाफ रेप और शारीरिक उत्पीड़न की शिकायत दर्ज कराई थी। आरोपों के अनुसार, आरोपी बिशप को काम के सिलसिले में अक्सर केरल आना होता था। इस दौरान उसने कई बार नन के साथ रेप की वारदात को अंजाम दिया। 👉एक रेप के आरोपी बिशप का जिसे वेटिकन ने भी उसके पद से हटा दिया हो ऐसा जोरदार स्वागत देखना देश की हर महिला को पीड़ा पहुंचाने जैसा हैं। 👉आखिर हम एक समाज के तौर पर किस तरफ जाना चाहते हैं? कैसा समाज और माहौल हम अपनी आने वाली पीढ़ियों के लिए छोड़ना चाहते हैं? 👉जिस देश मे बलात्कारियों का इतना भव्य स्वागत होगा क्या उस समाज में यह नैतिक साहस बचेगा की वह अपनी स्त्रियों के सम्मान के लिए खड़ा हो सके? 👉बहरहाल यह शर्मनाक घटना बताती हैं कि हम न्याय के नाम पर सिर्फ रेप पीड़ित महिलाओं के लिए मोमबत्ती ही जला सकते हैं, 👉इसके अलावा कुछ नही कर सकते। 👉 देश मे एक तरफ #metoo अभियान चल रहा और ऐसे समय रेप जैसे गम्भीर आरोप के मुजरिम का इस तरह जमानत पाना और उसका इस तरह से फूलमालाओं के साथ भव्य स्वागत इस पूरे मुहिम को तगड़े झटके की तरह है। 👉आपको याद होगा की जम्मू के कठुआ कांड में जब लोग सीबीआई जांच की माँग को ले कर सड़क पर उतरे थे तो उन्हें देश के वामपंथी धड़े ने ‘बलात्कारी’ बताया था। 👉यहाँ तक की खुद को बुद्धिजीवी कहने वाली लेफ्ट लिबरल जमात, और बॉलीवुड की कुछ अभिनेत्रियां हाथो में प्लेकार्ड लेकर ‘देवी-स्थान’ ‘हिन्दू’ जैसे शब्दों के साथ ट्विटर पर उतर गई थी लेकिन अब इस रेप के आरोपी बिशप पर सभी लोगो ने मुंह मे दही जमा रखी हैं 😡

👉बहरहाल यह शर्मनाक घटना बताती हैं कि हम न्याय के नाम पर सिर्फ रेप पीड़ित महिलाओं के लिए मोमबत्ती ही जला सकते हैं , 👉इसके अलावा कुछ नही कर सकते। 👉 देश मे एक तरफ अभियान चल रहा और ऐसे समय रेप जैसे गम्भीर आरोप के मुजरिम का इस तरह जमानत पाना और उसका इस तरह से फूलमालाओं के साथ भव्य स्वागत इस पूरे मुहिम को तगड़े झटके की तरह है। 👉आपको याद होगा की जम्मू के कठुआ कांड में जब लोग सीबीआई जांच की माँग को ले कर सड़क पर उतरे थे तो उन्हें देश के वामपंथी धड़े ने ‘ बलात्कारी ’ बताया था। 👉यहाँ तक की खुद को बुद्धिजीवी कहने वाली लेफ्ट लिबरल जमात , और बॉलीवुड की कुछ अभिनेत्रियां हाथो में प्लेकार्ड लेकर ‘ देवी-स्थान ’ ‘ हिन्दू ’ जैसे शब्दों के साथ ट्विटर पर उतर गई थी लेकिन अब इस रेप के आरोपी बिशप पर सभी लोगो ने मुंह मे दही जमा रखी हैं 😡

text:
october 23 talk. atoa.org for details.
dr. gail levin #author #critic and #art historian and professor of art history at the cuny graduate center moderates a panel considering the impact of the #metoo movement in the #contemporary #visual art world. 
panelists: #suzanneanker, chair, bfa fine arts department, school of visual arts
#nancyazara, artist
#kathygoodell, artist

organized by: douglas i. sheer, co-founder and chair of #atoa. 
nancy azara is an american sculptor. her work is carved, assembled and highly painted wood with gold and silver leaf and encaustic. the wood, the paint and the layers that make up the sculpture record a journey of memory, images and ideas.

kathy goodell is a new york painter and sculptor, currently living and working in the hudson valley. born in san francisco, schooled at the san francisco art institute, in the late seventies, she established herself as a leading figure among young artists in california that were interested in breaking down the barriers between mediums, removing #sculpture from its confines of the pedestal and painting from its traditional formalities. her current practice expands her repertoire, is more painting based, while maintaining her maverick status as an alchemist looking for the revelatory. she is an inventor of processes often going to extremes to achieve a metaphysical effect, defying taboos of the painters’ methods.
name: ArtistsTalkOnArt

text:
मैं भी, मैं भी, मैं भी. a @bbchindi report.

#metoo, #metoo, #metoo
पिछले साल अक्टूबर में अमरीका से शुरू हुआ #metoo अभियान जब भारत पहुँचा तो महिलाओं ने सोशल मीडिया पर अपने साथ हुए यौन उत्पीड़न के बारे में बताना शुरू किया.
तब किसी को ये अंदाज़ा नहीं था कि भारत में भी #metoo कैंपेन इतना बड़ा हो जाएगा कि बड़े-बड़े लोगों की छवि पर प्रश्नचिह्न लग जायेंगे.
भारत में पिछले अक्टूबर से इस अक्टूबर तक में बहुत कुछ बदल गया है. सोशल मीडिया पर तैरने वाले नन्हे से हैशटैग #metoo को भारतीय महिलाओं ने आज अपना 'युद्धघोष' बना लिया है.
लेकिन हर मुहिम की तरह इस पर भी शक़ किया गया और अनगिनत सवाल उठाए गए.  हैरत की बात नहीं है कि अभी महज एक महीने पहले ही कई लोग तंज़ कसते हुए, कुटिल मुस्कुराहट के साथ पूछते नज़र आ रहे थे- 'लेकिन #metoo से होगा क्या?' यही सवाल दोहराते कुछ लोगों की आंखों में असली चिंता भी दिखती थी.
एक बड़े वर्ग को ये चिंता थी कि कहीं ये कुछ दिनों का इंटरनेट ट्रेंड बनकर न रह जाए.
लेकिन अब ये कहना अतिशयोक्ति नहीं होगी कि कुटिल मुस्कानों को भी #metoo का जवाब मिल गया है और उन्हें भी जो वाक़ई इसके हासिल को लेकर चिंतित थे.
#metoo का हासिल क्या है, इसका जवाब कुछ इस तरह दिया जा सकता है: मोदी सरकार में इस्तीफ़ा
यह #metoo की ताक़त और हासिल ही है कि एमजे अकबर को विदेश राज्य मंत्री के पद से इस्तीफ़ा देना पड़ा. वो भी उस मोदी सरकार में, जिसमें ये दावा किया गया था कि 'इस सरकार में इस्तीफ़ों की परंपरा नहीं है'.
''नहीं... नहीं इसमें मंत्रियों के त्यागपत्र नहीं होते हैं भैया. यूपीए सरकार नहीं है. ये एनडीए सरकार है.''
देश के गृहमंत्री राजनाथ सिंह के बड़े आत्मविश्वास के साथ दिए गए इस बयान की हार #metoo का हासिल है.
भारतीय राजनीति के इतिहास में ऐसा पहली बार हुआ है जब किसी सरकार में किसी मंत्री ने यौन उत्पीड़न के आरोपों की वजह से इस्तीफ़ा दिया है.

मैं भी, मैं भी, मैं भी. a @bbchindi report.

#metoo, #metoo, #metoo
पिछले साल अक्टूबर में अमरीका से शुरू हुआ #metoo अभियान जब भारत पहुँचा तो महिलाओं ने सोशल मीडिया पर अपने साथ हुए यौन उत्पीड़न के बारे में बताना शुरू किया.
तब किसी को ये अंदाज़ा नहीं था कि भारत में भी #metoo कैंपेन इतना बड़ा हो जाएगा कि बड़े-बड़े लोगों की छवि पर प्रश्नचिह्न लग जायेंगे.
भारत में पिछले अक्टूबर से इस अक्टूबर तक में बहुत कुछ बदल गया है. सोशल मीडिया पर तैरने वाले नन्हे से हैशटैग #metoo को भारतीय महिलाओं ने आज अपना 'युद्धघोष' बना लिया है.
लेकिन हर मुहिम की तरह इस पर भी शक़ किया गया और अनगिनत सवाल उठाए गए.  हैरत की बात नहीं है कि अभी महज एक महीने पहले ही कई लोग तंज़ कसते हुए, कुटिल मुस्कुराहट के साथ पूछते नज़र आ रहे थे- 'लेकिन #metoo से होगा क्या?' यही सवाल दोहराते कुछ लोगों की आंखों में असली चिंता भी दिखती थी.

लेकिन अब ये कहना अतिशयोक्ति नहीं होगी कि कुटिल मुस्कानों को भी #metoo का जवाब मिल गया है और उन्हें भी जो वाक़ई इसके हासिल को लेकर चिंतित थे.

देश के गृहमंत्री राजनाथ सिंह के बड़े आत्मविश्वास के साथ दिए गए इस बयान की हार #metoo का हासिल है.
भारतीय राजनीति के इतिहास में ऐसा पहली बार हुआ है जब किसी सरकार में किसी मंत्री ने यौन उत्पीड़न के आरोपों की वजह से इस्तीफ़ा दिया है.
यह #metoo का हासिल है. पूरा ब्लॉग पढ़ने के लिए bbchhindi.com  पर आएं, ब्लॉग का लिंक bio में भी है. #metoo #timesup #women #discrimination #india #sexualharassment #harassment

text:
gente, la violencia es real.
en otro contexto, una mujer con las piernas abiertas, un hombre parado frente a ella, sus dedos en la vagina de ella y otra gente viendo la escena, se llama violación grupal. en un hospital se llama parto (wtf?).
las mujeres la están pasando mal en los servicios de salud sexual y reproductiva. no es sólo salud materna. cuántas veces no me han contado las mujeres que sus gines les dijeron que si no planeaban ser madres, no era tan importante sanar sus miomas o sus ovarios poliquísticos, como si lo único para lo cual tu salud como mujer más o menos importa es para tener bebés. cuántas mujeres no me han dicho que sus gines les dijeron que era normal que les doliera la regla (sic!)? cuántas mujeres no me han comentado que ya no saben qué hacer porque se sienten agotadas, distraídas, con insomnio, con regla irregular y sus gines les recetan la pastilla anticonceptiva para ser “regulares” y ya? cuántas veces no he escuchado a mujeres quejándose de resequedad vaginal y sus gines diciéndoles que no hay problema? o al revés, cuántas mujeres no tienen ni un resultado positivo en el papanicolau y ya les hacen la colposcopía y biopsia, por si acaso, ignorando los lineamientos que dicen que no son recomendadas en esos casos?
y en salud materna: las #parteras nos la pasamos conteniendo a mujeres que salen del sistema de salud traumadas, asustadas, sin entender, con ayunos prolongados porque las tienen esperando horas para consulta, estresadas porque les dicen que están gordas y seguramente tienen diabetes, sin mirar sus estudios.
estoy harta de escuchar la violencia, de tener que abrazar a mujeres paniqueadas, de escuchar que qué amable soy porque ser amable, tratar con paciencia y respeto debería ser la puta norma!! me alegra enormemente que las mujeres encuentren conmigo, con nosotras una burbuja de paz, de tranquilidad, de respiro. me agota sostener esa burbuja a veces. nos tenemos que preguntar seriamente cómo hacer para que las burbujas donde la atención está centrada en las mujeres y sus procesos fisiológicos, se hagan costumbre.
#metoo #violenciaobstetrica #ibelieveher #womenmatter #midwivesmatter #yabasta #hastaquelaburbujasehagacostumbre

text:
[let’s do it] alright, here we go. i am now officially collecting 3in x 1yard fabric strips from women who have experienced abuse, assault, silencing, harassment, or less pay at some point in their lives (1 strip per person) to make what i am calling #theboundblanket . please mail fabric to britney winn lee | p.o. box 4745 | shreveport, la | 71134., or if you’re local, drop it off to me. the goal of this piece is to demonstrate visually and artistically why an era of women speaking up is so powerful for changing the narrative of what it means to be female (and male) in this world. it could even be a good activity for your churches to work on;) my arms—and super large crochet needle—are open to receive these pieces of you 💚 please share widely.
.
.
.
#metoo #metoomovement #believewomen #believesurvivors #fridaymood #equality #loveyourneighbor #loveyourfemaleneighbour #instagood #postthepeople #art #artistsoninstagram

text:
flash back friday to the spring/summer of 2017. this picture makes me so sad, i remember sobbing before hand, then he asked to take my picture so i put on a smile and let him. why? i don’t know. i was so stupid, starving myself, barely getting out of bed, believing the lies he was feeding me everyday, i found safety in my bed and then he took that away from me too. but that is what it is like to live with a narcissist,  a sociopath. today a sexual assault case sits on the district attorneys desk waiting to be read, a month ago i received an order of protection against him from the courts, and yesterday i found out he wants to appeal this order. after a 6 hour court hearing,  5 of which was my testimony i cannot believe he would continue to try and victimize me. why can’t he just let me go? with everything that has happened with the #metoo movement to the #believeher movement how can such evil men continue to try and abuse women. boys won’t just be boys, those boys grow into men who manipulate and feel entitled to abuse. why must he continue to try to be an active participant in my life? 90 pounds, that is how much i weighed in the depth of his abuse towards me, isolated and alone, 90 pounds of nothing. a little over a year later i am putting my life back together, continuing to go to school, going to therapy every week, working towards what it means to have a healthy relationship not only with myself but with my partner as well who of course is affected by my abusers attacks toward me. 
this man owns a business, a child molester roaming free, continuing to abuse and abuse the legal system for his gains. when will these injustices stop?
our society is failing, failing women, failing our children, all for what? to protect men who abuse their power? 
we all know that men like this feel like they can do these things after the injustice of kavanaugh being voted in and trump being our president. 
i want to say that voting will take care of this but we all know to well that isn’t true, communities must be made aware of who is lurking behind the masks of self proclaimed “good men”. #fbf #selflove #selfcare #narcissisticabuse #orderofprotection #survivor #recovery #psa

text:
‌for a very long time, we have been discussing about various issues related to women. this made me curious to look for all the possible actions and measures that can be taken against it. so, let's focus on the remedies this time. what are the rights of women and legal remedies in this regard? ignorance is one of the main cause of tolerance. there are lots of sexual crimes that are being ignored by many of us as we consider them trifle or common but they are not trifle in the eyes of law. the scope of indian penal law is extremely wide in terms of sexual crimes (after amendment of 2013) and they are considered as the crime against whole of the society and not the victim only. for instance....
‌
‌1- [sec 294] of ipc prescribes up to three months imprisonment for doing any obscene act or singing any obscene song to a woman in a public place. ‌2- [sec 354] for the imprisonment (not less than a year that may extend to 5 years, and fine) for assault or using criminal force to outrage modesty of a woman. ‌4- [sec 354a] that deals with sexual harassment prescribes that... ‌any man committing any of the following acts—
‌(i) physical contact and advances involving unwelcome and explicit sexual overtures; or
(ii) a demand or request for sexual favours; or ‌(iii) showing pornography against the will of a woman; or (iv) making sexually coloured remarks, ‌  shall be guilty of the offence of sexual harassment.
‌for the offence specified in clause (i) or clause (ii) or clause (iii) he shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to 3 years, or with fine, or with both.
‌and for clause (iv) shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to 1 year, or with fine, or with both.
‌4- [sec 354b] provides for the imprisonment (not less than 3 years which may extend to 5 years and fine) for assault, abetment, or use of criminal force with an intent to disrobe a women or compelling her to be naked. ‌ << continue in the first comment...>>

text_retweet:
♥️⚖️♥️ #repost @najwazebian : tears. it was full of tears. i sat in the audience, listening to @rosemcgowan speak about her book, brave. about the bravery that it takes to share your story. about the traumas that we carry inside of us and how they wake up within us. about how sharing your truth will get you excluded in many spaces but it doesn't mean that you shouldn't.

i was sitting in the front row, shaking on the inside. just an hour before, i had written a poem that described a defining moment in my life. that moment was deciding to hit enter on my story.
i wrote it while attending my friend @inqlife 's poetry workshop. 
i struggled so much with having that poem written without sharing it. it felt like a story that needed to leave me. that needed to be shared.

q&a period comes and i'm getting more and more nervous.

i raise my hand. and as i start talking, my while body starts shaking on the outside. my voice starts shaking. that, my friends, was the trauma of sharing my story coming out into the world. 
i ask rose: "would you give me the safe space to be brave and share a poem that i just wrote that describes the moment of me sharing my story?". of course, she said.

and i start reading from my journal. and i could hear others around me crying. i could feel the silence in the room. but i was getting lighter and lighter the more i read.

it's like i didn't know how much i needed to speak about that moment. the moment i hit enter.

rose and the audience opened their arms wide open for me to share my heart. and i am so grateful. my heart is so full.

i cried. so. so. so much. but it was a cry of relief. a cry of release.

i invite you here to write a poem. just as @inqlife asked me to do, that describes a defining moment in your life. and just like @rosemcgowan offered that safe space to share, i offer you that here too. be brave. let it leave you so you can heal.

i can't wait to read your poems. they don't have to rhyme or look nice. just let them tell the truth of you. 
#hoffoundation #metoo

text:
bollywood hero sushant singh rajput got embroiled in a sort of #metoo controversy owing to some unclaimed allegations that he has harassed the heroine of his upcoming film 'kizie aur manny'. a report has earlier surfaced that he is troubling heroine sanjana sanghi and the girl complained to her parents about the same.

many got stunned to see sushant's name in that, and before that, director of kizie aur manny, popular casting director mukesh chabra, got sacked from the project temporarily after he also faced a couple of such allegations. reacting on all this, sushant felt quite emotional and stated that he is feeling sad to reveal personal information to defend himself and felt that there is no other way. 
revealing his sms chats from the first till the last day of the shoot, sushant revealed some screenshots and clarified that a hate campaign is being run against him. he stated that twitter didn't remove a blue tick from his account as rumours are being spread that twitter removed blue tick of his account due to the #metoo allegations. 
on the other hand, heroine sanjana is yet to respond to the whole fiasco and remained unavailable for a comment.

#sushanth singh rajput#santana sanghi#mukeshchabra.

text:
poetry
-----------------
the red dress, 
slit into half.
and the red wine.
red is our blood,
and so i guess it's fine.

the black winged liner,
perfectly lined.
and the fire.
black is the beauty,
and so is my attire.

the blue rose,
in the bouquet.
and the endless sky.
blue is the ocean vast,
but i never ask you why.

the yellow sun,
shining so bright.
and the the mustard grown.
yellow is the sunflower blooming,
and the smile unknown.

the pink lips,
glowing nude in light. 
and the book i bought.
pink is the color of a lady,
and that's what we have been taught.

i'm the blue, i'm the black.
i'm the yellow, i'm the pink.
i'm the syllable you read, 
and i'm the poetry dipped
in lavender ink.
i'm the purple, i'm the tangerine.
i'm the turquoise, i'm the green.
i'm the lady with a kind smile,
and i'm the hidden demon,
evil and mean.
i'm the red, i'm the indigo.
i'm the vibgyor of the rainbow.
i'm everything that you don't know.
i'm little. i'm more.
i'm the surface. i'm the core.
i'm the life. i'm the death.
i'm the poetry lying underneath.

___________________________

being myself as a woman^ - @agathaa.writes
name: She Speaks For The CHANGE ♀

yellow is the sunflower blooming,
and the smile unknown.

the pink lips,
glowing nude in light. 
and the book i bought.
pink is the color of a lady,
and that's what we have been taught.

i am the blue, i am the black.
i am the yellow, i am the pink.
i am the syllable you read, 
and i am the poetry dipped
in lavender ink.
i am the purple, i am the tangerine.
i am the turquoise, i am the green.
i am the lady with a kind smile,
and i am the hidden demon,
evil and mean.
i am the red, i am the indigo.
i am the vibgyor of the rainbow.
i am everything that you do not know.
i am little. i am more.
i am the surface. i am the core.
i am the life. i am the death.
i am the poetry lying underneath.

___________________________

text:
i was gifted this memoir by a dear friend whom i visited in purulia,  as a lasting memory of the beautiful town and the beautiful time we had spent there. there is no better occasion than today to share this, as ma durga is leaving us at the end of the almost ten day long celebration of bong madness. with a heavy heart, evidently, and with utmost reluctance we are bidding her goodbye, wishing subho bijaya to each other and bracing ourselves for the monstrous monday. well,  all good things come to an end but the best part is the countdown for 2019 pujo has already begun in our crazy heads. asche bochor abar hobe. 😊

meanwhile and almost ironically, while we are celebrating the biggest festival of women power in the city and beyond, #metoo is happening. i could not have ended this post without mentioning how it will potentially change the dynamics of indian cinema. hearing horrific stories, i think more and more people irrespective of gender, place, creed, should come out and speak, debate, support this movement. it's been hitting the right chords till now and hopefully we will come out as an evolved society from all this. more power to women in this journey. 
#durgapuja 
#womenpower 
#solidarity

text:
thanks to @themuchomama & @shandys_balanced_life for posting this!
feels so good to talk to my younger self. and tell that scared and and angry little girl know it will be ok. 
to my younger self: 
age 2....i know you're in foster care right now, but the family really does love you. don't be scared. one day you'll see treasured photos from a family you can't remember.
when you're 9...things will be scary, and terrible things will happen to you. you are so strong and will overcome them! but the memories will always be there....they make you who you are. #metoo
i'm sorry you are in dirty clothes a lot of the time. and the other kids pick on you....it won't be like this forever.
always rememeber what it felt like to see your mom hurt by a man, never let a man hurt you then keep him around...ever.
guess what?? you will finally meet your dad one day...and actually form a relationship!!
one day your siblings will be your only family....keep them close and love them with everything.

by 13 you will have met the girls that will become your lifelong friends. cherish them!
your first love/ marriage will not be your last...
you'll get a 2nd chance and it'll be everything you had wanted and needed in the past 💕
and oh those kids....your children will be your world..💕
be the adult to them that you needed someone to be for you growing up...💕
and i know you can't see it now, but you will truly love yourself one day. i promise. 💕
#whatiwanttotellmyself
#whatiwanttotellyou

text:
it’s hard to pick up a #newspaper or turn on the #news these days and not learn about a new public figure or company that is wrapped up in a sexual #harassment scandal.
in fact, the stakes are even higher for young #companies when it comes to sexual harassment issues. one chip at the company reputation could kill it before it even gets workshop started. through this #workshop india accelerator and lawyered seek to #educate the attendees on what is the law on posh, what constitutes sexual harassment, 
what are the consequences of sexual harassment and what are the rights and #duties of the #employees working in an #organization. the workshop will also deal with a 
few other #legal #issue that #startup may face and how to deal with such issues effectively.

the workshop will be hosted on 23-oct, 2018 
venue: india accelerator - 336 udyog vihar phase 4, gurgaon
8700922866

we look forward to a fruitful discussion and dialogue with you.

since then, the hashtag has became a rallying cry against sexual harassment, with multiple women coming out with their #metoo stories
for all those stories please visit

text:
what a day! today i’m so grateful because i was able to give my talk on marketing strategies for podcasters... but this was the first time that i weaved in my deeply personal story into the “business talk” as well.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am finding it more and more important to define my why in everything that i do. every decision i make. every event i attend. every friendship i put energy into. the list goes on and on.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
so in my #wearepodcast speech today i shared my “why” with the audience.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i allowed myself to be vulnerable.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i allowed myself to be imperfect.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i allowed myself to fail.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
when i told the story of losing first my mother and then my father to cancer, my voice faltered.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my palms were sweaty.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ my hands were shaky.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but i got through it. i shared how the driving force behind my business, my podcast, my book and my film were the deep loss that i suffered and my dedication to my mission of helping people realize that their health is in their hands.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that the body is able to heal itself if given the tools that it needs to do so.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that when we choose to turn our trauma into triumph and pain into purpose...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
everything can shift
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i’m humbled and grateful to share my truth at wearepodcast. when we speak our truth and stand in our power, we are unstoppable. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#foodheals #loveheals

text:
sometimes it's difficult to understand how much and in which way you are exhausted. it can mentally, emotionally or even physically but all you can do think about it is how terrible you feel and how nothing is ever going to be right. that's what i'm going through right now but you know what? i won't give up.
i'll continue to strive because i know i deserve something much better than what i have right now. i'll try my best to to do atleast one productive thing everyday so that i don't feel useless and unwanted.
that's what i planned to do. i'm not giving up so easily. #exhaused
