text:
i have no shame in speaking on behalf of my mother who endured a lot of abuse all her life. people ask why they kept quiet for so long. have you ever been endured to abuse? the abused always believe they are at fault. this is why many keep quiet for years before they speak up. they are conditioned to keep shut. 
the other side is many who just use the system. please don’t do that. you take away the credibility of those who have been abused and are looked upon with mistrust when they report because of a few bad apples. you abuse the system the system will abuse you back. and this post is not gender specific. please speak up! 
sorry maa posting this publicly without your permission. we’ve had enough. love you! 
#metoo #mymomtoo

text:
a broken girl. 
an abused girl. 
a sufferer from anxiety & ptsd. 
a lost human. 
a single mom of 3, 
a girl who was all alone . •
•
who is overflowing with gratitude, love, joy, hope, peace, excitement, and abundance! •
i have never been more thankful for the people in my life, my business, my partners, my family, my god, my future. •
i have intentionally crafted where i am today, and who i am today. 
none of this has happened on accident. 
but through taking gods words, in who he says i am, i have been able to live with purpose and step out of my comfort zone, take big risks, transform my identity, and change the course of my life. •
you are not defined by your circumstance , what’s been done to you, or what you have done... jesus came and paid the price of that... so free yourself, and begin walking with purpose in who god says you are! •
•
•
•
•

a gem of a person, a true gentleman, a man with the kindest heart.

text:
för ett år sedan spred sig #metoo över hela världen. i egypten har rörelsen öppnat upp samtalet om sexuellt våld, då fler pratar om sina upplevelser i sociala medier. men grunden för rörelsen lades tidigare, av aktivister som belyste de brutala gruppvåldtäkterna på tahrirtorget t ex, säger feministen mozn hassan. hon har vunnit right livelihoodpriset för sitt arbete, men nu har hennes organisation, nazra - for feminist studies, fått sina tillgångar frysta.

📷: @ceciliauddenm

text:
kobe bryant kicked off jury of la’s animation is film festival after #metoo outcry

kobe bryant kicked off jury of la’s animation is film festival after #metoo outcry
gkids pulls former lakers star after online petition surfaces, notes 2003 rape accusation jeremy fuster 1:49 pm getty
kobe bryant was removed wednesday from the jury of this weekend’s animation is film festival. the move followed an online petition that called on the festival to do so due to the retired nba star’s 2003 rape accusation.
bryant received the academy award for best animated short earlier this year with famed animator glen keane for the film “dear basketball,” based on the essay bryant published on the players’ tribune announcing his retirement in 2015.
but with the #metoo movement center stage in hollywood, bryant’s nomination and subsequent victory earned criticism from sexual abuse activists who pointed out his much-publicized sexual assault case 15 years ago, when a woman accused him of raping her in a colorado hotel room. bryant confessed to adultery but denied the assault accusation. criminal charges were dropped after the accuser declined to testify, with a civil suit being settled out of court. also read: film academy nixes kobe bryant for membership despite oscar win
a change.org petition set up by an organization called women & allies called on animation studio gkids, which sponsors the festival with the annecy international film festival and variety, to remove bryant from this weekend’s proceedings. as of this writing, the petition has 141 signatures.
“in light of the #metoo movement, there has been little to no recourse for kobe bryant’s actions of sexual assault,” reads the petition. “we demand that gkids, variety, & annecy revoke their complicity in enabling a sexual predator to continue a life without any accountability both as an individual and a celebrity.”
“on its website ‘animation is film’ specifically states one of their primary purposes is to champion and support women filmmakers . it’s time to turn these words into action. text:
a 17 year-old nursing student was reportedly drugged and raped by  a b-pharma student, dilshad and a relative yatinder, who is a ward boy in bagpath district's government hospital on tuesday. the girl was undergoing a treatment at the hospital while the incident took place. the accused allegedly took advantage of the absence of victim's sister who went to get refreshments, late in the night. both the accused and her uncle were arrested shortly thereafter.
on further probing, she narrated that sedatives were injected by the ward boy and that, she woke up to consciousness, in middle of night while the men were assaulting her. she immediately kicked them off and raised an alarm. 
the accused are penalized under ipc  section 376 d (gang rape) and 328 (causing hurt with intent to commit an offence) and section 3 and 4 of posco act, said superintendent shailesh kumar pandey.
chief medical officer dr. sushma chandra reported that, yatinder and the accused student’s, diploma is cancelled. a further inquiry, headed by a three-member panel has been set up in this regard.

picture source : www.indianexpress.com

text:
true leaders embrace the fact that life is messy and their team will be messy sometimes. human beings are not robots simply meant to do-the-work. true leaders lean in to this, how uncomfortable it may be,  and i call it heart-centered leadership. a heart-centered leader leads their team with compassion, values authenticity, and embraces vulnerability because they know that that's the space where the magic happens. success matters, but not at the cost of your team’s health. .
join me today for a free virtual roundtable discussion at 11am pst / 2pm et to talk in depth about heart-centered leadership and the paradigm shift in today's leadership (link in profile)
.

text:
the measure of any society is how it treats its women and girls,” -- michelle obama. @taranajaneen, unlocking the #metoo movement one year ago has been one of the most culture pivoting moments of the decade. we salute and thank you beyond measure! it was pleasure to meet and thank you for your impact on not only the lives of many globally, but mine specifically.
_________________________________________

empowering black and brown girls and women to break their socially accepted silence and allow for healing is your god given calling. victims remain victims because there was no place or platform to heal. being a strong black woman has always meant being able to bare the brunt of what comes our way, to remain poised in the face of opposition and to trudge forward without looking back. although this is true, #metoo has unlocked a safe space for women of color everywhere. again, thank you!

kwan entertainment founder anirban das blah, a popular bollywood celebrity manager, couldn't escape the wave of india's one of the biggest movements, me too. he was asked to step aside from his position in the wake of sexual misconduct allegations against him. “we have asked anirban blah to forthwith step aside from his duties, activities and responsibilities at kwan, its subsidiaries and affiliates with immediate effect,” said a statement issued by the entertainment and marketing company. all this hasn't gone down well with him as he tried to commit suicide today. #metoo #insta #instanews #bollywood

text:
speaking at the un safe cities equality for women event this week was a big deal for us. @cityofedmonton hosted this parallel event to hear from a few folks how we’re building a safer city in #yeg. the conversation about sexual violence in hospitality and arts is a tough one to crack, but we’re chipping away. i was so grateful to hear an intersectional approach from the other presenters, as the title of the event missed non-binary/genderqueer folks. their safety matters too, especially as trans women and marginalized groups experience sexual violence at a higher rate than cis, white women. we can’t leave anyone behind in this conversation. i’m currently in the very lengthy process of beginning a non-profit to push this conversation forward. as i put the pieces together slowly, and figure out how to shape this to include as many voices as possible, i keep hearing more stories and a greater need for this initiative. stay tuned for some updates very soon (finally!). thank you for your support and encouragement. let’s build something impactful together! 💪🏼
.
.
.
#yeg #yegdt #yegequality #unwomen #safercities #edmonton #sexualviolence #metoo #takecareofeachother

text_retweet:
#repost @planetmidori
• • •
about vulnerability, rage, art, and speaking truth and power from our darkest souls.  pls read. #repost @bmoreart ・・・
did you know the autobiography behind this painting?? “gentileschi (1593-1653) was an exceptional artist. she was the first woman to be accepted into florence’s prestigious accademia delle arti del disegno, and caravaggio’s only female follower. she was raped, when she was 17, by her painting tutor, agostino tassi. when tassi refused to marry her (the only way to restore her reputation), her father took him to court. the young gentileschi testified against her rapist and endured torture to prove her honesty. tassi was sentenced to exile, though the punishment was not enforced.

in the wake of the rape and trial, gentileschi made two paintings of judith cutting off her enemy’s head. both are intensely physical, and the second is especially gory; you can almost feel the resistance of flesh to blade. scholars have noted that judith looks a lot like gentileschi, and holofernes a lot like tassi, making the paintings self-portraits of a rape victim’s revenge. during and after the kavanaugh confirmation hearings — in which the judge denied dr. ford’s accusations against him — people shared images of the artworks with and without comment. beyond the rage was a hunger for interpretations of sexual assault from the point of view of survivors.” excerpt from female artists are grappling with sexual violence in their work by @jilnotjill in the @nytimes #femaleartists #rape #metoo #artemisiagentileschi #nytimes #artreview #bmoreart

i̇ş annesi’nin üstünde ayrıca bir de doğum kilosu baskısı var.
peki kadınların benlikleri kilo ve boydan ibaret mi?
i̇ngiliz oyuncu ve televizyon sunucusu jameela jamil, kadınların toplumda sadece dış görünüşleriyle değerlendirilmelerinden bıkıp, instagram’da @i_weigh hesabını açtı ve kadınların tartıdaki sayılardan ibaret olmadığına dikkat çeken bir hareket başlattı. 
hesap, bu yılın başından bu yana 178b takipçiye ulaştı.
biz de bu hareketi bütün kalbimizle destekliyoruz.

text:
the streets are singing the songs of destruction,
gender is walking in the cocoon of fear,
we are all caterpillars of the past ,
wearing a plastic skin of stains ,
amidst the changing technology,
our heart is a silent graveyard,
holding the tiny graves of redemption,
welcome to the 21st century ;
here modern leeches dressed in fake modesty,
rape your soul everyday ,
and if you raise your voice ,
you are being called so uncool ,
let's bury humanity and visit another planet,
because every creature has been dismantled,
o ! son of adam hear those who can't speak,
their eyes behold the share of #metoo !
©annies_enigma
.
.
@writersnetwork @mirakee @iamjass @ariachez @geraldine_mary @hiyasays @lovenotes_from_carolyn
#pod #metoo
.
.
dear mirakeeans,
many people wanted me to write about the #metoo. being a girl i would easily correlate it with females but i believe every individual (be it male or female) ,every creature who can't speak ,even animals who were raped have their #metoo stories. so ,this is dedicated to all those. we all have our #metoo stories ,small or big ,let's not generalise this with females. let every creature suffered be heard through this. 
love & light
.

.

text:
"we live in a dangerous time."
the words come from not only his orangeness, but also from horace engdahl; ancient member of the swedish academy, and also old friend of the now-convicted jean-claude arnault who will serve two years in prison following a massive amount of allegations from the women he sexually assaulted for decades.
.
and the response has been furious. which i somewhat find a bit odd. because if it's true, it should be considered good news in an indirect manner. one could dismiss the sentence above as the kind of pouty arrogance you can find in a sore loser, but i don't.  those are the words of someone whose usual entitlement to vile acts has turned into fear. their usual arrogant sense of control turned into fury and bitterness. and this is exactly what they should be feeling. just imagine what it takes to make someone who for decades has thought themselves to be untouchable and able to get away with anything to say something like that. i sure do hope we live in a time where it's dangerous to be someone like them.

text:
en 2018, en france, je suis une femme et je suis libre de m’exprimer, de voter, de conduire, d’étudier, d’épouser un homme ou une femme que j’aime, de divorcer, de travailler, de pratiquer la sorcellerie, d’être infidèle, de faire de la politique, de découvrir mes jambes et mes épaules, de tomber amoureuse, de prendre la pilule, de me faire avorter, de m’offrir ou de me refuser.

néanmoins, en 2018, en france, les statistiques en termes d’agressions et de violences envers les femmes sont affligeants. 
je remarque avec étonnement que le mouvement metoo n’a pris de l’ampleur que l’année dernière, tout comme je remarque, cette année, la mobilisation de plus en plus forte en matière d’environnement. pourtant, les femmes sont écrasées sous la domination masculine depuis...toujours ? pourtant, certains ont tenté de nous prévenir du réchauffement climatique il y a déjà plus de dix ans...non ?
peut-être que l’urgence de vivre est enfin là. peut-être que l’énergie féminine, en résonance avec la terre, a besoin, enfin, d’éclore. peut-être  qu’une certaine force de vie, énergie créatrice, est enfin écoutée. je crois en cette énergie, en ce qu’elle peut apporter de doux et de sensible, d’intuitif, d’empathique. je crois en la liberté que nous pouvons avoir, en tant que femmes, d’être qui nous sommes, de célébrer le fait d’être femme comme nous l’entendons. de nous exprimer avec nos qualités et nos défauts, notre fragilité et notre puissance. je crois en cette force que nous avons, mais que nous n’osons pas toujours accueillir ; parce qu’on ne nous a pas appris, et parce qu’on a pu nous étouffer, nous abîmer, nous ignorer.
je crois que les hommes sont nos alliés. pas tous, bien sur. mais nous avons la capacité de les reconnaître, ceux-là, si nous le voulons. et de développer, ensemble ou séparément, l’énergie féminine qui circule en chacun de nous. 
pour éviter que nos petites filles aient un jour à dire «me too ». • #femme #fille #france #liberte #respect #feminin #énergie #feminisme #mouvement #metoo #violence #mobilisation #urgence #force #creation #vie #terremere #intuition #celebration #energiefeminine #photography #blackandwhite #photographie #noiretblanc #enfant

peut-être que l’urgence de vivre est enfin là. peut-être que l’énergie féminine, en résoce avec la terre, a besoin, enfin, d’éclore. peut-être  qu’une ceaine force de vie, énergie créatrice, est enfin écoutée. je crois en cette énergie, en ce qu’elle peut appoer de doux et de sensible, d’intuitif, d’empathique. je crois en la libeé que nous pouvons avoir, en tant que femmes, d’être qui nous sommes, de célébrer le fait d’être femme comme nous l’entendons. de nous exprimer avec nos qualités et nos défauts, notre fragilité et notre puissance. je crois en cette force que nous avons, mais que nous n’osons pas toujours accueillir ; parce qu’on ne nous a pas appris, et parce qu’on a pu nous étouffer, nous abîmer, nous ignorer.
je crois que les hommes sont nos alliés. pas tous, bien sur. mais nous avons la capacité de les reconnaître, ceux-là, si nous le voulons. et de développer, ensemble ou séparément, l’énergie féminine qui circule en chacun de nous. 
pour éviter que nos petites filles aient un jour à dire «me too ». •

text:
opera queensland's don giovanni at playhouse, qpac was absolutely breathtaking on opening night!

quick run to get your tickets to this classic and important show only at qpac until 3 november, get tix at qpac.com.au 
spoiler alert below.
•
•
•
review: duncan rock plays the title role and very much becomes the 'monster' all feel, especially the women! his voice was remarkable and charming which gave the story that little bit extra. the costumes, lighting and staging was magnificent.

the whole cast and queensland symphony orchestra was sensational and you could feel the intense emotion  throughout the entirety of the famous mozart opera.

set in the victorian era (where jack the ripper once lurked), the themes of lust and heartbreak were intertwined with the tragic story of don giovanni as he preys on innocent women and commits heinous crimes for his own personal pleasure and vindictive game.

this show is particularly relevant in the current climate with the #metoo movement and the ongoing issues of sexual assault.

right at the conclusion of the show, around 67 of the women that duncan's character, don giovanni assaulted or raped all came onstage, most physically and emotionally naked. it was a glorious moment to watch them take him to his weakest point and show the world what he had done to share that pain and release with the audience as they came together in solidarity.

go see this brilliant piece of opera now and see our interview with duncan rock in link in bio.

#dongiovanni #opera #operaqueensland #theatre #duncanrock #brisbane #brisbaneevent #atqpac

text:
being able to wake up to these two everyday is such an amazing feeling. 
for the first time, i am in a respectful and loving relationship that truly fulfills my needs. 
learning to recognize the love you deserve isn’t easy. i spent almost 11 years in various toxic and abusive relationships. even after a year of being with the most loving human, i’m still getting used to it. i’m still surprised that he wants to hold my hand anytime we’re out. that he wants to cuddle with me at night or when watching tv. that he will gladly walk the dog with me, fix up the apartment, clean, etc. he never makes me feel guilty for asking for help with something. 
everyone deserves someone who will love them the way they need to be loved. don’t accept anything less 💖

#borderlinepersonalitydisorder #bpd #relationshipgoals #toxicrelationships #abusiverelationships #recovery #depression #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness #anxiety #endthestigma #survivor #metoo

tw: mention of sexual misconduct// a series of everyday breach of consent▪️
"my family and i went on a trip to amritsar when i was 15, and we went around touristing and sight-seeing. in the afternoon, my brother and i decided to explore on our own, since our parents were shopping. we were roaming in these cramped streets when, out of the blue, this person came close and trailed us for a bit. in a particularly crowded spot, he put his hand on my back and said something that loosely translated to- "i'll meet you tonight", while staring at my breasts. i freaked out, but thankfully my brother noticed that man as well. we left the street as quickly as possible, and entered a shop and waited for our parents instead. it was unsettling."
.

text:
ruby rumie's monumental wall of portraits lugar común positions the relationship between women across class-divides in colombia by stripping the sitters of jewelry and fashion which might otherwise announce socio-economic status. these portraits serve as a way of visualizing the often unacknowledged intimate relationships and connections between women who clean, work and live in the same household.

last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.

fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation.

text:
the manhattan district attorney's office has told harvey weinstein's attorney that the lead detective in the movie mogul's sexual assault case advised an alleged victim to delete messages from her phone before turning it over to prosecutors.

the bombshell revelation comes less than a week after the office dropped part of the case against weinstein, after evidence emerged that the same detective had coached a witness to stay silent about evidence that cast doubt on the account one of weinstein's three accusers.
#news #harveyweinstein #newsyoucanuse #metoo

text:
« je ne fais pas de différence claire entre l’orgasme pendant que je me touche et celui que j’expérimente lors d’un acte sexuel ». pour meli, la masturbation fait aussi partie de l’acte. et elle le revendique. « dans ce moment que l’on partage à deux, chacun peut participer à procurer du plaisir à l’un ou à l’autre. c’est un travail d’équipe », sourit la lausannoise, bientôt la trentaine.
.
se toucher pendant l’amour, « c’est hyper beau, je trouve aussi beau dans l’autre sens d’ailleurs ».
.
pour meli, l’orgasme est une expérience que son corps lui procure. « ce n’est pas l’autre personne qui va me le donner, c’est l’autre personne qui va aider à ce que mon corps me le donne », ajoute-t-elle encore.
.
>>> écouter le récit de meli
.
« enfant, je me masturbais. un jour ma mère m’a dit: ‘tu sais, c’est que les garçons qui font ça’. en tant que femme, je pense qu’elle ne pouvait pas assumer devant moi qu’elle, aussi, faisait cela. et du coup, toute mon enfance, je pensais que je faisais quelque chose que les garçons font ».
.
selon meli, s’il est plus facile de jouir pour un garçon que pour une fille, c’est « parce qu’on leur explique beaucoup plus tôt comment leur corps fonctionne. par conséquent, leur droit à jouir, il est plus clair », avance-t-elle.
.
« si on apprenait aux filles à se connecter à leur corps, en leur disant que c’est ok de se masturber, de jouir ; si on leur apprenait qu’elles ont un clitoris, et comment il fonctionne, je pense que ça serait plus facile. chacun a le droit de se découvrir, de se s’observer, de se toucher ».
.
méli s’est assez rapidement identifiée aux revendications des mouvements #metoo et ‘t’as joui’, « mais sans pour autant que ça soit révélateur : j’avais déjà entamé le chemin de déconstruire et revendiquer ». quand elle s’est abonnée à la page ‘t’as joui’, elle a tout de même été choquée de constater « à quel point les discours proposés étaient des relations sexuelles hétéronormées classiques: un homme qui couche avec une femme. ce n’est pas inclusif. il y a beaucoup d’autres genres, beaucoup d’autres sexualités ».
.
🎤+🖍: @julieroncoroni
.

text:
worry is not love.  choosing worry thoughts is giving your true essence of love and empowerment away.  worry is energy that will never help or serve you, your loved one, or the greater good. .
.
you are strong, loving, and resilient.  be present in this moment. send love energy to yourself, or your loved one, or to the greater good.  if action can be taken, take it. not from worry. from love. from your inner strength. for the depths of your true self. .
.
you are worthy of releasing worry. you are enough. you have what it takes to love powerfully.  free yourself from the burden energy of worry. free yourself to fully love. ❤️
.
.

text:
“if you added up all the women who have been murdered by their husbands or boyfriends since 9/11, and then you add up all the americans who were killed by 9/11 or in afghanistan and iraq, more women were killed by their husbands or boyfriends” - gloria steinem. violence against women in america is a problem that is growing rapidly but little is being done to help. 
i read an article yesterday about how the #metoo movement has gained such momentum, but that there is a lack in talking about and supporting advocacy against domestic violence. there are social stigmas against talking about abuse, and a dv victim is often put in danger by calling out their abuser. 
i speak up despite my fears. i speak up for the women who can’t speak anymore. i will continue to speak up until i see change. .
.
.
.
.

آدره لورد نظریه پرداز فمنیسم تقاطعی نویسنده و شاعر و یکی از الهامبخشترین زنان فمنیست میگه：برای زنانی مینویسم که حرف نمیزنند.برای زنانی که بخاطر ترس و وحشت صدایی ندارند چون به ما یاد داده شده که به ترس بیشتر از وجود خودمان احترام بذاریم.چون به ما یاد داده شده که سکوتمان نجاتمان میدهد.
آدره لورد به نکته خیلی خوبی اینجا اشاره کرد.زنان همیشه در طول سالها و قرنها تشویق به سکوت شده اند.همیشه به آنها گفته شده که سکوتشان به نفعشان است که اگر ازار جنسی دیده اند بهتر است سکوت کنند تا ابرویشان نرود یا اگر کتک خورده اند سکوت کنند چون طبیعت مرد خشن است.به زنان گفته شده که اگر مورد ازار و سورفتار و خشونت قرار گرفته اند احتمالا خودشان تقصیر داشته اند.که ذات زن اینگونه است که مغلوب باشد.و بعد نظامهای مرد سالار سیستمها را جوری طراحی کرده اند که اگر زنی جرات شکایت و اعتراض داشته باشد هزینه دهد.نظامهای قضایی که وقتی زنان وارد آنها میشوند تا دادخواهی کنند،زنان را میجوند و تفاله هایشان را دوباره به آغوش مردسالاری پس میدهندد.به طور کلی در تمام سیستمهای تبعیض آمیز از برده داری گرفته تا آپارتاید و مرد سالاری،نظریه پردازان این نوع نظامها تلاش کرده اند دلیل تبعیض و خشونت علیه عده ای از ذات خود قربانیان معرفی کنند و با این حربه به قربانیان القا کنند که سکوت و کوتاه آمدن بهتر از اعتراض است.وقتی ذات زن را لطیف و مهربان و ظریف تعریف میکنی آنوقت زنی که خشمگین شود و اعتراض کند ایراد دارد!هیس!سکوت کن!خانوم باش!
_برای زنانی که فکر میکنن سکوت نجاتشون میده،ولی اینطور نیست.زنانی که مورد آزار جنسی قرار میگیرن و جرعت ندارن به کسی بگن(خودم بارها و بارها تجربه کردم ولی الان دیگه ۱۶ ساله نیستم)
_برای همه دخترایی که لباس زیرای آزاردهنده میپوشن و کل روز به قفسه سینشون فشار میاد و تنگ نفس میکشن برای جنس مخالفی که حاضر نیس یه روز لباس زیری بپوشه که اینطوری آزارش بده.(مثلا به بیضه هاش فشار بیاد)
_کسانی که بکارت زن براشون یه ارزشه.که زن اختیار تن خودشو نداره.حتی عقل هم نداره باید خودشو حفظ کنه برا مردی که معلوم نیست کجاس اونم با اجازه پدرش 
_کسایی که ۵ صب پامیشن با دقت ارایش میکنن که زیباتر به نظر برسن.از هیکل و صورتشون ناراضین و پی جراحین.
(تو به تنهایی کافی و زیبایی و بدون  که شجاعت مسریه❤️)

#girlpower #youareenough #believeinyourself #womenpower #womenrights #feminism #feminist #beauty #metoo

text:
utilizar las redes sociales no es sólo un pasatiempo; constituyen también la posibilidad de multilocalizar nuestros mensajes, colectivizar nuestras emociones y atemporalizar las conversaciones. el ciberactivismo se enmarca en este contexto y consiste en la utilización del correo electrónico, blogs y redes sociales para hacer pública una causa a través de la diseminación veloz de la información que permite la internet. 
el ejemplo más temprano de ciberactivismo fue organizado por el grupo conocido como the zippies, en 1994, en gran bretaña. esta acción se conoció como intervasion of the uk y consistió en enviar correos electrónicos masivos para protestar contra el proyecto de ley que penalizaba las fiestas de música electrónica al aire libre. 
en la última década se han construido importantes procesos políticos y sociales a partir del ciberactivismo, como el movimiento 6 de abril en egipto( 2011); el 15-m o movimiento de los indignados en españa (2011); manzana 1 en bolivia (2013), #yosoy123 en méxico (2012) o #metoo, en eeuu (2017). en colombia también hemos visto como las redes sociales fueron fundamentales tanto en el plebiscito por la paz como en las recientes campañas presidenciales, así como han frenado importantes nombramientos del gobierno actual, como el de maria javier pacheco para el centro nacional de memoria histórica o claudia ortiz para la unidad nacional de protección.

#ciberactivismo #movimientossociales #cambiarelmundo #redessociales #internet #15m #cienciassociales #comunicación #cienciasdelacomunicación #sociologia

text:
chegou a hora de passar este ponto, alto e claro.

o tantra não é algo que você "pega" dormindo com um professor ou curador.

a melhor maneira de incorporar o tantra é com suas próprias práticas e exercícios de oficina.

se você tentar "pegar" o tantra fazendo sexo com alguém em posição de autoridade sobre você, certamente haverá confusão.

a menos que você esteja completamente livre de traumas, sólido em seus limites, claro o que você quer, e totalmente fortalecido em sua sexualidade ... é melhor não se envolver sexualmente com uma figura de autoridade.

os riscos são que você será acionado em antigas memórias de tempos em que uma figura de autoridade se aproveitou de você.

você pode se sentir incapaz de expressar seus limites da mesma maneira que um amante de poder.

você pode se sentir confuso depois ... essencialmente, é importante saber que você não precisa ter o sexo para aprender tantra!

o tantra é na verdade a arte de usar sua energia sexual para impulsionar estados superiores de consciência.

você pode mover essa energia por conta própria, usando práticas tântricas específicas.

por favor, não desista do seu poder, esperando que alguém o salve, cure ou ilumine.

só você pode fazer isso!

text:
több mint 200 tininek tartottam ma összesen 4 eladást szexuális zaklatás/erőszak és testképzavarok/#bodypositivity  témákban.
rengeteget készültem rá, és még soha nem volt bennem ennyi kétség: érdekli majd őket? megértik majd? fontos lesz nekik? túl sok, ha sokkolok, túl kevés, ha nem?
elég jó leszek? 
aztán pár hónap vívódás után úgy döntöttem: önmagam leszek, őszinte leszek, és ennyi.

és figyeltek. és részt vettek. és úgy tűnt, értik. és amikor azt mondtam: akkor most elmesélem a saját történelmet, minden idegszáluk rám fókuszált.
a végén pedig többen odajöttek, és őszinteséget adtak cserébe, olyan témákban, amelyekről korábban hallgattak. 
megérte. ♥️ talking about the #issues of mine. i had 4 speeches today about #metoo and #sexualharrasment / #eatingdisorders and bodypositivity, more than 250 teenagers were listening. 
i was so confused... so nervous before. but i decided to be #myself and to be honest. to shere my stories with them as they happened. 
and it worked. 
they were listening. they were thinking. and they shared their #stories too.
i feel love and gratitude, i'm so happy! 🙏honesty for #honesty, that must be the right way.
.
.

text:
it’s time.
it’s time we stopped running,
it’s your turn now.
for all those days you chased us,
now pack yourself up.
run from all the hands and nails, 
waiting to rip you,
in all the places you touched.
sprint away before we are close.
you may not see another dawn,
if we make you feel what we felt.
did you ask before you started?
now we aren’t asking you either.
#timesup
#metoo

text:
the last few weeks have been enormously triggering. as the #metoo movement in india gains fierce momentum driven by women displaying enormous courage and coming forward with their stories, the stage is set for real change. much needed change. 
i’ve been spending a lot of time introspecting and revisiting parts of my past i’ve long buried. as a wave of anger, hurt, hope and strong emotion washes over me i’ve found solace in my fitness routine. working off some of my anger has helped me cope with the onslaught of emotion bubbling up. this is my version of self care and i hope in these difficult times you find your version too 💖 #strengthconditioning #plank #selfcare #core #coreworkout #calisthenics #shoulderworkout #upperbody #smallbutstrong #fitnessblogger #veganfitgirl #girlswholift #fitnessaddict #fitspo #sweatitout #girlgains #thesweatlife  #strongnotskinny #strongereveryday #gymlife #yogagirlslift #gymbunny #fitstagram #fitchick #goaldigger #workoutmode #goodvibesonly #limitlessme

text: sen jag startade mitt konto på insta har jag minskat prostitutionen, slutat med droger, minskat mitt alkoholintag och lyckats bli normalviktig och känna tillit till andra människor igen. det viktigaste av allt har varit gemenskapen, för innan var det som att leva i skuggorna, i marginalerna, i skymundan. nu har jag hittat många som också levt i samma mörker och vi har slutit samman. jag har insett att min situation inte är unik och att jag inte är ett hopplöst fall bara för att livet är svårt. när jag ser mina systrar ser jag mig själv och känner en kärlek och förståelse gentemot er/dom som jag försöker använda som redskap när jag förlåter mig själv. #intedinhora tog mig från skuggan in i ljuset, från en knuten näve i fickan till en högt upphöjd mot himlen. vår gemenskap, att vi backar varandra och ser och hör varandra är allt. så många år jag gått i kylan på gatorna i göteborg och tagit för givet att jag var den enda i världen som sålde sex i bilar och köpte knark för pengarna. så många år jag känt mig döende och ensam som tändsticksflickan med kokain i väskan och en avundsjuk blick på medelklassfamiljer. så många år jag gömt mig i något hörn på rosenlund och kommit ut ur skuggorna bara för att säga vad jag kostar till första bästa man. den tiden är över. gemenskapen i #intedinhora är viktig. för ett år sedan hade jag ingen oas, ingen röst, inget hopp, inga synliga systrar. idag har jag mycket av allt. jag tänker mer på mitt eget värde nu än för ett år sen. för jag ser inte bara less. det är inte less dom köper. det är alla som är i min situation, mina systrar, som jag aldrig tidigare mött. och det är inte okej. nu när jag känner er känner jag mig. och jag vet hur jävla värdefulla vi är. #metoo #prostitution #utanskyddsnät #intedinhora

text:
abuse was a word i would never have associated with my life, despite having been touched by it in different ways.
the first instance was in college. at a classmate's hostel room, when i fell asleep from fatigue. i was woken a later by someone groping and kissing me. my instant thought - hell he's done what he wanted, i'm effectively soiled. & why tell anyone, why would they believe me esp when i'm not even sure it's abuse - it was "just" groping. i told myself it can't be abuse cuz i let him get away with it.

years later, the ceo of my company behaved extremely inappropriately with me. i told couple of male colleagues- they shrugged it off saying yea he's known for that, just stay away from him. we'll even help to ensure you're never alone with him. so i shut up. couple of months later, 2 new hires faced the same issue and went straight to hr. due to that 7 of us in total finally spoke up and told the hr our story. they did the right thing and escalated it. we got to have meetings with the cfo one on one, that's when we realised the sham it was. the meetings were designed to shut us up individually with different tactics. i personally was told, you didn't go to hr for 6 months, maybe you're lieing just to hurt him. i left immediately and never returned to that building. i started to understand abuse and it's ugly faces then. but, he'd only touched me suggestively, never violated me physically, would that then really be abuse?

the final straw was the person i was supposed to marry. 2 instances of sadistic domestic abuse, where i was beaten mercilessly and almost choked to death once, and months of intense emotional abuse where my self worth was shattered systematically - and i finally knew for sure the meaning of abuse. 
one of the very important parts of the movement is that it has defined clearly for young girls, what the different degrees of abuse are, and how to recognise it. and the conversation it has started will hopefully also lead to women being better equipped to handle it in the moment if it still happens. 
#metoo #timesup #empoweringwomen #neveragain

text:
anna burns named first northern irish man booker prize winner | 
17 october 2018

congratulations to society of authors member anna burns, who has been named the winner of the man booker prize 2018 – a first for a northern irish writer, and the first female winner of the prize since 2013.

the book follows an 18-year-old girl, known only as middle sister, as she describes the predatory advances of ‘the milkman’ in belfast during the troubles, and has been hailed as a book of its time amidst the #metoo movement.

text:
så ett år efter #metoo och jag vill förtydliga att det pågår. det händer än. så vad har hänt? 
jag är positiv, jag ser skillnader. dels så får jag fler å fler uppdrag från mansdominerande branscher och fler män i rummen när jag föreläser. oftast dock, är beställaren en kvinna i den mansdominerade branschen. #metoo har helt enkelt gjort det svårare för män att avfärda kämpande kvinnors kamp för förändring. och vad är bättre än att gräva där vi står? insidan vår egen box.
jag hör fler å fler män höja sin röst och fler projekt med perspektivet maskulinitet får pengar för att nå fler män. jag delar analys med många. mäns gränsöverskridande beteenden är problemet och att fler män engagerar sig och säger ifrån blir därför en del av lösningen. 
en rädsla jag haft utifrån den problem-och-lösnings-analysen är att debatten alldeles för ofta handlar om symptomen och alldeles för sällan om själva strukturen. när vi pratar om enskilda mäns handlingar så blir lösningen enskilda mäns handlingar. jag längtar efter kollektiva, strukturella lösningar. 
jag längtar efter hockeyförbundets och fotbollsförbundets svar på #metoo och sponsorers uttalade krav på föreningar och ambassadörer. jag längtar efter lärarförbundets och skolinspektionens krafttag. jag längtar efter handlingskraft som förändrar tid och rum.

vi har samsynen, mäns våld mot kvinnor förstås inte längre som ett importerat problem utan klarsynt som ett imiterat problem. att män befordras, får huvudroller, får dela ut nobels priser, får spela i landslag, sitta i tv-soffor, fronta tv-produktioner, bredbent tala till punkt i tv-soffor, skriva böcker, får sponsorer, chefsroller och riksdagsplatser inte bara trots en historia av sexuellt våld eller andra gränsöverskridanden utan ibland också tack vare... det är problemet och har alltid varit. män som ser upp till andra män, ger dom möjligheter och rättigheter att ta ut svängarna. vänskap till vad pris som helst. det är problemet,det andra är symptom av längtan att tillhöra, bekräftas, älskas, status, makt, beundran eller som i horace engdahls fall en kombo av brist på sjukdomsinsikt och ren självbevarelsedrift med våldstäktskulturmannen som stilförebild. #insidanboxen™️

jag är positiv, jag ser skillnader. dels så får jag fler å fler uppdrag från mansdominerande branscher och fler män i rummen när jag föreläser. oftast dock, är beställaren en kvinna i den mansdominerade branschen. #metoo har helt enkelt gjort det svårare för män att avfärda kämpande kvinnors kamp för förändring. och vad är bättre än att gräva där vi står? insidan vår egen box.
jag hör fler å fler män höja sin röst och fler projekt med perspektivet maskulinitet får pengar för att nå fler män. jag delar analys med många. mäns gränsöverskridande beteenden är problemet och att fler män engagerar sig och säger ifrån blir därför en del av lösningen. 
en rädsla jag haft utifrån den problem-och-lösnings-analysen är att debatten alldeles för ofta handlar om symptomen och alldeles för sällan om själva strukturen. när vi pratar om enskilda mäns handlingar så blir lösningen enskilda mäns handlingar. jag längtar efter kollektiva, strukturella lösningar. 
jag längtar efter hockeyförbundets och fotbollsförbundets svar på #metoo och sponsorers uttalade krav på föreningar och ambassadörer. jag längtar efter lärarförbundets och skolinspektionens krafttag. jag längtar efter handlingskraft som förändrar tid och rum.

vi har samsynen, mäns våld mot kvinnor förstås inte längre som ett importerat problem utan klarsynt som ett imiterat problem. att män befordras, får huvudroller, får dela ut nobels priser, får spela i landslag, sitta i tv-soffor, fronta tv-produktioner, bredbent tala till punkt i tv-soffor, skriva böcker, får sponsorer, chefsroller och riksdagsplatser inte bara trots en historia av sexuellt våld eller andra gränsöverskridanden utan ibland också tack vare... det är problemet och har alltid varit. män som ser upp till andra män, ger dom möjligheter och rättigheter att ta ut svängarna. vänskap till vad pris som helst. det är problemet,det andra är symptom av längtan att tillhöra, bekräftas, älskas, status, makt, beundran eller som i horace engdahls fall en kombo av brist på sjukdomsinsikt och ren självbevarelsedrift med våldstäktskulturmannen som stilförebild. #insidanboxen™️

text:
"we need to start with our sons, our uncles, our fathers, grandfathers and really let them know that, as women we shouldn't have to teach other women how to be safe... and that what we have is not an invitation.

women should be able to exist without the fear of any man"

there are nights where i stay up fearing for my niece and her innocent naivity that has the potential to be violated.

i long for the day that abused women are vindicated. a day were women dont shame other abused women. a day were having to remember the *exact* day you were raped is not important, because you were raped!

#cherylzondi #metoo #supportabusedwomen #womenyouarewarrior #abetterday #god

text:
✨✨luminárias de led sem fio metoo!!✨✨
.
aquela momento da madrugada que o bebê resmungou, perdeu a chupeta, chorou e vc precisa ir no quartinho mas não quer acender a luz forte nos olhinhos deles... como faz?! 🤷🏻‍♀️
. 
é só acender a luminária fofa de bichinhos da metoo!
. 
acendem com um simples toque das mãos. 
tem a luz suave para não prejudicar os olhinhos do bebê.
.
além de luminária, serve como um lindo adorno para o quartinho!
.
ou também pode ser usado no quarto da criança que está na fase de medo de escuro, monstro, como o meu filho. como ela tem uma luz bem fraquinha, não atrapalha o sono da criança e ela não fica com medo se acorda no meio da noite.
.
super prática, não tem fio. .

text:
friday night rant.

i am so sick and tired of hearing excuses. “i can’t give up meat, i need protein” 🖕 “animals don’t have feelings or emotions” 🖕 “cats and dogs are different” 🖕 “my meat is killed humanely” 🖕 “if i give thanks to the animal who died for me to eat, that makes it okay” 🖕 “it’s not illegal” 🖕 “it’s cheaper” 🖕 “you can’t be a health coach if you have such ‘extreme’ views” 🖕 “race horses enjoy their ‘job’” 🖕

these are all things i have had said to my face, unprompted. 🖕

no.

most people eat meat because of their tastebuds. 🖕

there is no difference between you eating a dog, or a cow. 🖕

there is no difference between you eating a cat, or a pig. 🖕

there is no difference.

in this day and age, it’s time you step up, and make a difference. care about beings other than yourself.

ethical. environmental. 
i expect this post to be mostly ignored, people don’t want to acknowledge the damage they’re doing. i get it. it’s hard. 
instead of scrolling past, have your say, have a debate. don’t just sit back and ignore.

raise awareness. 🙌🐥🐷🐮🐣🐴🐗🦆🐍🐙🐠🐑🐈🐕🐇🦃🦌🐎 #health #vegan #nutrition 
@moby @stellamccartney @rob____banks xxxxx

text:
monte is going to nottingham (the unesco city of literature) in january to perform at the madhatters, to show how you can turn your survivor story into a piece of art and beauty that can be an inspiration for others. part of the income from the event will be donated to the maggie's centre which provides free support for people with cancer and their families. she will talk about her upcoming book and how her writing and work within the theatre scene helped her turn her fights as a sexual and physical abuse survivor into the very thing that changed her life and became this beautiful adventure and fairytale she lives everyday. from norway to the uk.  to read more about the maggie center, click link in bio.

text:
the hindus say that without shakti, the personified feminine life force, shiva, who encompasses the masculine ability to act, becomes a corpse. she is the life energy that animates the male principle, and the male principle in turn animates action in the world.” ~ clarissa pinkola estes

the personified feminine life force (shakti) reminds the personified masculine life force (shiva) that we are a force of interdependent nature first and independent humans second.

what does this mean, exactly? to put it into darwinian terms, it means that we are, first and foremost, social creatures. we need each other to survive. as such, competition has always been secondary to cooperation; otherwise we wouldn’t have survived as a species.

if we wish to continue our survival as a species, it is vital that we allow cooperation to be superior to competition. this means cooperation with the environment as well (shakti as gaia). shakti is here to remind shiva of this fact. to restore the balance. to make sure he isn’t “pretending to be asleep.” the problem is that many people, intellectuals and nonintellectuals alike, have confused darwin’s discoveries by focusing primarily on competition, and concepts like “might makes right.” similar to the way the nazis hijacked (and falsely portrayed) nietzsche’s overman concept, the modern war machine has hijacked (and falsely portrayed) darwin’s “might makes right” concept.

this has created a dangerously lopsided view of reality: a kind of conquer-control-destroy-repeat mindset that has permeated our culture to such an extent that it has falsely convinced people that war is necessary to keep the peace and that violence is the answer to the problems we face. #justdoit #views #mondaymotivation #work #workout #trip  #yoga #namaste #vegan #food #fashion #love #ocean #meditation #nba #self #selfie #me #beach #universe #club #friday #selfhelp #toronto #420

text:
from day to day.... you never know what life may bring.... next week, i start my fourth cycle of chemo. i started out with 6 cycles. i'm a little more than half way through. 
in the valley you find lots of things, you find fear, you find sadness, you find doubt, you find abandonment, you find embarrassment, you find depression, you find disbelief, and with each day you find wonder.... through all those things, make sure you find faith in god. no matter thee out come, finding faith, will eventually lead you to find the real you. 
thanking god for the valley, because somewhere in there are answers, dont come back to the surface the same. fight! remember cancer doesnt have to be ugly! love yall happy fearless friday #almostbald #ifight

text:
if you can't see
the look of dread
if you can't hear
my raging screams
if you look at me with,
doubt
judgement 
disbelief 
disdain 
if you discount,
my stories
our stories
the stories of victims
if you shift the focus 
from #metoo
to #notallmen
get over yourselves 
rise up,
wake up,
time's up!

over the last week, i've seen the #meetooindia movement sweeping across the country. i deliberately stayed away till now, because yes it opens up few incidents that i wish had never happened, few that i've yet not spoken of publicly but just in the safe space of immediate family, but i realise how important it is to hold hands today and share our stories.

they might disgust you, again. make you relive the pain, the anger, again. but sharing your story, will not only relieve you of the burden of shame that perhaps you have been carrying all alone, but just might give courage to someone in need today, who can stand up against injustice, who will find their voice and shout out loud, 'no means no'.
.
linking in bio, an article i wrote for @dna_india in 2014. four years later, i still have the same questions. but i also have hope!
.
.

.

text:
don’t use people as a punching bag because they have the right to punch you back 🥊🥊. it’s called self-defense. it’s auto reflex like a knee-jerk. shape up or ship out. it's that simple. this applies to both sexes. check previous post. —————————————————————-

text:
#metoo wird zu #masaktach: frauen in marokko gegen sexuelle gewalt

gegen die weit verbreitete gewalt gegen frauen gibt es eine immer größer werdende bewegung in marokko. einige sprechen vom #metoo der marokkanerinnen. ihr slogan heißt #masaktach - das bedeutet "ich schweige nicht". #masaktach richtet sich gegen die machokultur und dagegen, dass opfer von vergewaltigungen sich oft auch noch schämen. wie "the middle east eye" erklärt, ist das diktat der "hchouma", der schande noch weit verbreitet - auch wenn unlängst ein gesetz gegen sexuelle belästigungen verabschiedet wurde.

das neue gesetz bestraft "belästigung, körperverletzung, sexuelle ausbeutung oder missbrauch von frauen". einige - wie die ehemalige ministerin nouzha skalli - finden, dass auch die neuen regeln nicht genügen, weil beispielsweise vergewaltigung in der ehe nicht unter strafe gestellt wird.

was hält ihr von dem neuen gesetz?

https://de.euronews.com/2018/10/17/metoo-wird-zu-masaktach-marokanerinnen-gegen-sexuelle-gewalt

text:
please read the caption

this photo was taken months ago and i never posted it but i think now is the time.

last night i was sent a video by an instagram user of him masturbating. i had done nothing to encourage him to do so. he did not get my consent. this is sexual assault! me posting any sort of picture is not an invite for anyone to do this to me or anyone else. before sending someone something like this without consent, consider the fact that not only is this sexual assault and illegal but the person receiving it has a story; possibly of sexual abuse, mental health issues or triggers. this man gets to continue his day to day with no thought or concern. i am left picking up the pieces of my past resurfacing, nightmares and increased anxiety. 
don't feel sorry for me. instead take my hand and join me in the fight against online sexual harassment and abuse that men, women and non binary people face on a daily basis. you don't need to be a feminist to join the fight.

photo description: jessica is smiling and holding up a sign that reads: i need feminism because i am more than my body. she is wearing black frames glasses a green crop top and a yellow skirt.

#feminist #effyourbeautystandards #nomeansno #getconsent #girls #bodypositive #bopo #bodypositivity #metoo #awareness

text:
hot news
dituduh melakukan pelecehan seksual kepada sanjana sanghi, sushant singh rajput  membantah keras 😯

aktor bollywood sushant singh rajput , pada jumat pagi, menepis semua tuduhan pelanggaran seksual terhadap dirinya dengan berbagi screenshot percakapan teksnya dengan rekan mainnya di film "kizie aur manny" sanjana sanghi . “hal terakhir yang patut dilakukan adalah mempertahankan diri dari fiksi yang diciptakan oleh sebuah agenda. orang-orang yang menggunakan kampanye yang sangat dibutuhkan ini untuk agenda pribadi mereka terlalu banyak untuk diabaikan. jadi disini adalah percakapan teks dengan sanjana sampai waktu saya syuting untuk film. saya membiarkan anda memutuskan”, tulis sushant dalam tweet yang dibagikan pada kamis malam. namun dia akan menghapusnya, nanti.

sushant berbagi screenshot baru pada jumat pagi. “saya merasa sedih untuk mengungkapkan informasi pribadi tetapi tampaknya tidak ada cara lain untuk menyatakan apa yang dibutuhkan pada kampanye ini. dari yang pertama hingga hari terakhir syuting, inilah yang terjadi di lokasi syuting dengan sanjana”, tulis sushant dalam tweetnya.

teks pertama adalah dari 9 juli dan teks terakhir adalah dari 22 agustus. screenshot menunjukkan obrolan ramah antara sushant dan sanjana dimana mereka terlihat berbicara tentang pemotretan dan penampilan mereka secara umum. 
lencana verifikasi twitter sushant dikatakan telah diambil oleh twitter india karena kampanye #metoo baru-baru ini. aktor ini mengklarifikasi bahwa akunnya belum memiliki centang biru sejak 5 september. "dan untuk semua orang yang sengaja menggunakan tanda centang biru twitter yang hilang, untuk membuktikan klaim palsu mereka, izinkan saya untuk mengatakan bahwa itu tidak ada sejak 5 september. maka periksa dulu sebelum memberikan kesimpulan bahwa anda sangat ingin mengusik", dia menulis. 
laporan dari media adalah sushant telah menggoda sanjana dan membuatnya merasa tidak nyaman dan telah terjadi sejak lama. juga dikatakan bahwa orang tua sanjana sanghi harus campur tangan setelah sutradara mukesh chhabra tidak mengambil sikap. 
mukesh chhabra men-tweet..(selengkapnya baca difacebook) 😯
